<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="1TI" stage="Rev" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:00:52Z" when="2009-10-02 04:00:52Z" stage="Draft">1st draft from BIS by Pdt. Max Jacob; second pass April 2000 from CEV; TW3, UBS Trans. Handbook, Ex. Helps, Kroeger &amp; Kroeger for 1 Tim. 2:11-15; team revision in Darwin with Max, June &amp; Chuck September 2001; UNS check; Kupang, Gereja Paulus, 29-30 Jan, 2002; Chuck, Max &amp; Mus; Consultant check with David Glasgow and Max, Mus, and Chuck at Gereja Silo, Kupang, 23 April 2002; Gk notes added by Chuck Sept 2005, checked Christ &amp; devil ; further exegetical changes in Oct 2005 with Marge Crofts, Barbara &amp; Chuck marked with (***) ; final read thru for NT by Chuck;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:03:21Z" when="2014-02-24 11:03:21Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 22-23 April 2002 at Gereja Silo in Kupang; Consultant: David Glasgow, approved. Report: KM 1 Tim consltnt check.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-20 04:00:48Z" when="2015-01-20 04:00:48Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted a bit.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">1 Timotius</p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">1 Timotius<bt>1 Timotius</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat yang partama<bt>Paulus' first letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi dia pung tamán Timotius<bt>to his friend Timotius</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Salam<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Timotius yang bae!<bt>Dear Timotius!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Salam dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah su angka ame sang beta jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan. Deng kotong ada baharap sang Tuhan Yesus yang kasi kotong idop tarús-tarús deng Dia, tagal Tuhan Allah su kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala.<bt>Greetings from me, Paulus. God has appointed me to be Yesus Kristus' *emissary/envoy/apostle. And we-inc are hoping in the Lord Yesus, who makes/causes us-inc to live continually/forever with Him, because God has saved us-inc from our sins/wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tius! Lu su sama ke beta pung ana sandiri, tagal beta yang tunju jalan ko lu ju parcaya sang Kristus. Beta sambayang minta ko Tuhan Allah, kotong pung Bapa, deng Yesus Kristus, kotong pung Bos, kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae deng rasa kasian, deng kasi lu idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>Tius (=Tim)! Lu are just like my own child, because I am the one who showed the way/guided you so that you also believe in Kristus. I pray asking that God, our-inc Father, and Yesus Kristus, our-inc Boss, show/reveal Their goodness/kindness/grace and mercy, and give you a life of (or: allow you to live in) external peace, relational peace and inner peace. [EXEG: 3 aspects of Gk /eirene/. Cf CEG word study.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mercy = 1) putus ko sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">mercy = 1) putus ko sonde kasi jato hukum sang beta. 2) kasi sampat ko lu idop bebas lai (keep looking)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apostolos: sent-out-person, apostle, missionary, messenger, a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">apostolos: sent-out-person, apostle, missionary, messenger, a man who is sent with full authority, a group of highly honored believers with a special function, commissioned kata: according to, in accordance with, because of, in conformity with, corresponding to<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>epitagen: command, order swteros: savior, deliverer, preserver<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>elpidos: hope, expectation, waiting, expectation with certainty. The object of hope, the goal of our hope, the source of our hope, the reason for our hope, the one on whom we place our hope, he is our hope, we hope to see him and be like him, the foundation for our earnest yearning, our confident expectation, our patient waiting for full salvation LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by command of God our savior and Christ Jesus our hope<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>gnesiw: true, genuine, legitimate teknw: child, metaphorically; follows Filemon 10.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>pistei: faith, believing, what is believed or the act of believing xaris: grace, kindness, undeserved favor, gracious care or help, goodwill, a Greek greeting and leave-taking wish<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>eleos: mercy, compassion, pity, a greeting, tender affection ready to help the needy person eirene: peace, welfare, health, wholeness, tranquility, a Jewish greeting<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: to Timothy, true son in the faith; grace, mercy, peace from God the father and Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 16:1</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ati-ati deng orang yang kasi ajaran sonde batúl<bt>Be careful with people who give untrue/incorrect teaching/s</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tempo hari, kotong dua ada sama-sama di kota Efesus. Waktu beta mau pi propinsi Makedonia, beta dorong sang lu ko tenga di Efesus. Te itu waktu, ada orang-orang yang bekin bingung jama'at dong, deng ajar hal yang sonde batúl dong. Jadi beta minta ko lu pi kasi stop sang dong, ko dong jang ajar tarús bagitu.<bt>Back then, the two of us-inc were together in the city of Efesus. When I wanted to go to the province of Makedonia, I pressured you to stay in Efesus. Cuz (elaboration) at that time, there were people who were confusing the believers by teaching things that were not correct. So (consequently), I asked you to go (put a) stop to them, so they wouldn't continue to teach like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kathws: just as, just like parakalesa:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kathws: just as, just like parakalesa: to urge, ask, request, advise, encourage<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>prosmeinai: remain, stay poreuomenos: going, proceeding, travelling<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>hina: so that, in order that paraggellw: give orders, insist, command, direct<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>heterodidaskalein: different teaching, false doctrine LITERALLY: Just as I requested you to stay in Ephesus when I was going into Macedonia, that you should command certain ones not to teach other doctrines<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Deng orang dong ju buang-buang waktu parcuma deng pi basambung mulu deng carita dongeng omong kosong, deng basilat lida so'al daftar turunan yang sonde putus-putus pung. Hal macam bagitu dong cuma bekin orang dong babakalai, deng sonde bekin dong idop deng parcaya sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>And those people are also wasting time needlessly and arguing/squabbling over nonsensical fables/fairy tales/myths, and debating.in.nasty.detail endlessly about lists of descendants/ancestry. Those (sorts of) things only make people fight, and don't make them live and believe in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sesat = KM ~ BI ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">sesat = KM ~ BI ; kasi barenti = fire, pecat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mede: and not, neither prosexein: pay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">mede: and not, neither prosexein: pay attention to, devote attention to, give heed to, take notice of, spend time on<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>muthois: myths, legends, fables, senseless stories genealogiais: genealogies, list of ancestor names<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>aperantois: endless, long haitines: which<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>ekzeteseis: useless speculation, arguments, questions, controversies parexousin: cause, produce, promote<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>mallon: rather, instead of oikonomian: training, work, plan, building up, edifying. "Strong" is not what he's talking about. CHECK PARALLELS.<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>pistei: faith LITERALLY: neither to pay attention to myths and long genealogies, which cause arguments instead of the way of God which is by faith;<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Beta kasi nasiat sang lu ni, deng maksud ko biar ajar orang parcaya dong ko idop deng basayang dari hati yang barisi, dari pikiran yang lurus, deng dari parcaya yang sonde maen-maen.<bt>I give you this advice, with the intent/purpose that you teach believers to live in reciprocal love/pity from clean livers (=pure motives), from correct/straight thinking, and from faith/belief that is serious/not trivial/not playing around.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Use terms in lists uniformly in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">Use terms in lists uniformly in 5T's. telos: end, purpose, goal, aim, outcome<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>paraggelias: command, order, charge agape: love<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>katharas: clean, pure, unselfish kardias: heart<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>suneidesews: conscience, judging ourselves agathes: good<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>pistews: faith anupokritou: genuine, sincere, true; this is presented negatively as "without putting on an act, unfeigned, not a show, no shibai". LEX: no throw (da) ack.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: the purpose of the command is love from a clean heart, and a good conscience, and sincere faith,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma ada guru saparu yang su serong jao deng kasi tenga buang itu nasiat. Ais dong pi buang-buang waktu basambung mulu deng omong harba-biruk sa.<bt>But there are some teachers who have deviated far and abandoned that advice. So they go and waste time arguing and speaking without order/reason/pattern.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang sonde ada guna apa-apa deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">yang sonde ada guna apa-apa deng orang laen.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tines: same as &quot;get guys&quot; in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">tines: same as "get guys" in v. 3. astokheesantes: miss the mark, lose the way<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>eksetrapesan: turn away, turn aside, wander away, give up, swerve mataiologian: fruitless talk, useless talk, empty talk, foolish discussions<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: from which some have lost their way, turning aside to useless talk,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dong kasi tunju diri bilang, dong tu, guru yang ajar ba'i Musa pung Hukum dong. Dong bagaya jadi guru bésar, ma dong sonde tau yang dong ajar tu, apa.<bt>They point to themselves saying they are teachers who teach the Law of Gf Musa. They behave.in.the.style of important teachers/professors, but they don't know/understand what they teach.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bagaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">bagaya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal dong bagaya jadi guru mati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Padahal dong bagaya jadi guru mati pung, ma sonde tau yang dong ajar tu, apa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelontes: desire, want nomodidaskaloi: teachers of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">thelontes: desire, want nomodidaskaloi: teachers of the law<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>noountes: understand legousin: say<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>diabebaiountai: confidently affirm, assert, speak confidently, insist LITERALLY: desiring to be teachers of the law, they neither understand what they are saying nor what they insist on.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Kotong samua tau bilang, ba'i Musa pung Hukum samua, bae! Asal kotong pake sang dia iko Tuhan Allah pung maksud yang batúl.<bt>We-inc all know that all of/the whole Law of Gf Musa is good! As long as we-inc use it to follow/obey God's true purpose/intention.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oidamen: know kalos: good|i(8) (8) |rnomos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">oidamen: know kalos: good<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>nomos: law nomimws: according to the rules, lawfully, properly, in the right way<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>khreetai: use LITERALLY: But we know that the law is good if anyone uses it in the right way,<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Itu Hukum dong, bukan tulis kasi orang yang pung idop su batúl dong. Ma ada tulis kasi orang yang tukang marontak, yang sonde mau dengar parenta, yang idop jao dari Tuhan, yang suka bekin jahat, yang sonde nodek sang Tuhan, yang pandang enteng hal yang barisi, yang tukang bunu orang, deng yang bunu bekin mati dong pung mama deng papa sandiri.<bt>Those Laws were not written for people whose lives are right(eous)/correct/true. But it was written for people who are rebels/troublemakers, (those) who don't like to listen/obey commands, (those) who live far from God1, (those) who like to do evil, (those) who don't care.about/give.attention to God1, (those) who belittle/scorn/disparage things that are clean/pure, (those) who kill/murder people, and (those) who murder their own mother and father. [DISCOURSE: natural RL order.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eidws: know dikaiw: righteous, upright, just|i(9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">eidws: know dikaiw: righteous, upright, just<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>keitai: exist anomois: lawless, lawbreaker<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anupotaktois: undisciplined, disobedient, criminals, rebellious, unruly, insubordinate asebesi: godless, ungodly, irreverent. TERM: ack jalike God notting<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>hamartwlois: sinners, defies God by outward act anosiois: unholy, not religious, irreligious, lack of inner purity<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>bebelois: profane, scoffers, mockers, treat religion with contempt matrolwais: killer of mother<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>patrolwais: killer of father androphonois: murderer<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: knowing this, that the law does not exist for the righteous person, but for the lawbreakers and rebellious, irreverent and sinners, impure and scoffers, killers of mothers and killers of fathers, murderers,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Itu Hukum dong ada tulis ju kasi orang yang maen seks sambarang, yang homoseks, yang culik orang ko cari doi, yang tukang putar-balek, yang saksi dusta, deng kasi samua orang yang suka bamalawan deng ajaran yang batúl.<bt>Those Laws are also written for those who sexually reckless/arbitrary/haphazard/with anybody, (those) who are homosexual (loan: homoseks), (those) who snatch people to get money (covers both kidnappers and slave traders), (those) who often deceive/con artists, (those) who are false/lying witnesses, and for all people who like to oppose true/correct/right teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dursila = sexually immoral ; homoseks"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">dursila = sexually immoral ; homoseks = both ; kawe-kawe = Jawa (bencong) transvestite; germo = BI madam, woman who runs a brothel, bordello, cat house ; maen serong di luar-luar =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pornois: fornicator, sexually immoral arsevokoitais: male"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pornois: fornicator, sexually immoral arsevokoitais: male homosexual<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>andrapodistais: slave dealer, slave traders, kidnapper pseustais: liar<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>epiorkois: perjured, false testimony, swear a lie is the truth heteros: another of a different kind<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>hugiainouse: be healthy, sound, true didaskalia: teaching<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>antikeitai: be opposed, contrary LITERALLY: for sexually immoral persons, male homosexuals, kidnappers, liars, those who give false testimony, and any other thing contrary to sound teaching,<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ajaran yang batúl dong, datang dari Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, yang Dia sarakan kasi beta. Deng Tuhan tu, Allah yang talalu hebat. Orang pantas angka nae tinggi-tinggi sang Dia.<bt>Right teachings come from God's Good News, which He has given/turned.over to me. And that God1, is a God2 who is excessively incredible/impressive. It is appropriate that people praise (Idiom: elevate very high) Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euaggelion: good news, gospel dokses: glorious|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">euaggelion: good news, gospel dokses: glorious<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>makariou: fortunate, in a good state, blessed; NEB "eternal felicity". TERM. Not eulogeetos "people say good things about him or wish him well". episteuthen: entrust<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: according to the good news of the glorious and blessed God, which was entrusted to me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Dia pung hati bae<bt>Give thanks to God, because of His goodness/kindness/grace</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Beta minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, tagal Dia parcaya sang beta, deng bekin beta mampu kasi jalan Dia pung karjá.<bt>I give lots of thanks to our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus, because He trusted me, and made me able to carry.out His work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xapin: thank endunamwsanti: strengthen, give strength,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">xapin: thank endunamwsanti: strengthen, give strength, enable<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>piston: trustworthy, faithful, worthy egesato: consider, know,<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>themenos: appoint, put into dikonian: service, ministry<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who gives me strength, because he considered me faithful, appointing me for the ministry,</Message></Annotation><v n="13-14" />Padahal dolu beta suka omong bekin busuk ko kasi jato Yesus pung nama, deng bekin sangsara orang-orang yang iko Dia pung jalan idop. Beta suka tendes bekin ancor sang dong. Beta jahat bagitu, tagal itu waktu, beta sonde mangarti apa yang beta bekin, deng balóm parcaya sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus. Ma Dia sonde lupa sang beta. Deng Dia kasi tunju Dia pung sayang sang beta.<bt>Whereas formerly I often rubbished (Idiom: spoke making rotten to cuz (elaboration) to fall) Yesus' name, and caused suffering for the people who followed/obeyed His way of life. I often oppressed destroying them [NOTE: SVC action-resulting state]. I was evil in that way, because at that time, I didn't understand what I was doing, and [I] didn't yet believe in our Boss, Yesus Kristus. But He didn't forget about me [NOTE: has sense of lose track of or give up on]. And He showed His love/pity to me. [EXEG: later translations (NRSV, NLT, CEV) take sense of "violence", rather than "insolent", which better fits context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bajingan = jahat, kurang ajar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">bajingan = jahat, kurang ajar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proteron: earlier, in the past, formerly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">proteron: earlier, in the past, formerly blasphemon: blasphemous, slanderous, speak evil<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>diwkten: persecutor, religious persecutor hubristen: insolent, insult, injurious, violent<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>eleethen: have mercy agnown: be ignorant<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>epoiesa: do, act apistia: unbelief<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: formerly being a blasphemer and persecutor and violent; but I was shown mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief,</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:3, 9:4-5</note>Tamba lai, Dia kasi tunju tar abis-abis Dia pung hati bae sang beta! Dia kasi berkat tumpa-rua sang beta, ko beta bisa parcaya kuat sang Dia, deng beta bisa sayang orang dong sama ke Dia sayang sang beta.<bt>Furthermore, He never ceased showing me His goodness/kindness/grace! He gave abundant blessings to me, so that I could believe strongly in Him, and I could love other people just like He loves me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tumpa-rua = melimpa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">tumpa-rua = melimpa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huperepleonasen: be abundant, overflow xaris: favor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">huperepleonasen: be abundant, overflow xaris: favor, grace, goodwill<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: but the favor of our Lord overflowed with the faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Kotong su biasa dengar bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus Kristus su datang di ini dunya, ko kasi salamat orang yang bekin sala dong.&gt;&gt; Memang batúl bagitu! Dari samua orang yang bekin sala, na, beta ni yang paling jahat.<bt>We-inc have often heard that, “Yesus Kristus has come into this world to save people who have done wrong/sinned.” That is certainly true! Among everyone who has done wrong, na, I am/was the most evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistos: trustworthy, faithful, true, sure logos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pistos: trustworthy, faithful, true, sure logos: word, message<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>apodoxes: acceptance aksios: worthy, deserve<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>hamartwlous: sinner swsai: to save<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>prwtos: first, chief, foremost LITERALLY: The message is true and deserves full acceptance, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners; of whom I am first,<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Biar beta jahat bagitu, ma Tuhan Allah putus ko sonde kasi jato hukum sang beta. Te Dia mau pake beta jadi conto ko kasi tunju Yesus Kristus pung sabar kasi orang yang paling jahat sama ke beta ni. Deng bagitu, orang laen yang bekin sala dong ju bisa parcaya sang Dia, ko biar dong dapa idop tarús-tarús deng Dia.<bt>Even though I was so evil like that, nevertheless God decided to not hand down a sentence/punishment to me. Cuz (elaboration) He wanted to use me as an example to show Yesus Kristus' patience/tolerance to people who are most evil like I am. In that way, other people who do wrong can also believe in Him, so they can live continually with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: /sabar/ can be translated /hati besar/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mercy = putus ko sonde kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">mercy = putus ko sonde kasi jato hukum sang beta.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="endeiksetai: show, demonstrate, display hapasan: full,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">endeiksetai: show, demonstrate, display hapasan: full, unlimited, endless, perfect, utmost<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>prootooi: prime example, foremost makrothumian: patience, longsuffering, forbearance<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>hupotupwsin: model, pattern, example mellontwn: be about to<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: but because of this I received mercy, in order that in me first, Christ Jesus might show full patience, to be an example for those who were going to believe on him for eternal life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Puji Tuhan!<bt>Praise God1!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Cuma Dia sa, Allah;<bt>He is the only God2;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sonde ada yang laen lai!<bt>there is no other!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Raja yang parenta tar abis-abis.<bt>[He is the] Raja who rules/governs without end/eternally.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang idop tarús-tarús.<bt>He is the one who lives forever/continually.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang sonde kanál mati.<bt>He is the one who doesn't know death (=cannot die).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang orang sonde bisa lia deng mata kapala.<bt>He is the one who people can't see with their own eyeballs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua hormat deng puji kasi sang Dia,<bt>All honour and praise [is given] to Him, [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe salamanya!<bt>until forever!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Amin.<bt>Amin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basilei: king aiwnwn: eternal, of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">basilei: king aiwnwn: eternal, of the ages<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>aphthartw: imperishable, immortal, incorruptible aoratw: invisible<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>monw: only time: honor, respect<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>doksa: glory, praise LITERALLY: To the eternal King, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honor and glory forever and ever. Amen.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ana Timotius yang bae! Beta mau kasi tau sang lu, apa yang lu musti bekin deng lu pung tugas dong. Ini samua ni, iko apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su omong memang so'al lu pung diri. Kalo lu iko itu kata-kata deng batúl, lu tingka ke tantara satu, yang pintar baparáng, lawan yang jahat dong.<bt>Dear child (no age implication) Timotius! I want to tell/let you know what it is that you must do in your job/responsibilities. All these things are in accord with what God1's *spokesmen/prophets have foretold about yourself. If you truly follow/obey those words, you are like a soldier who is skilled in fight (wars/battles), opposing those who are evil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareggalian: from verse 3 &amp; 5"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pareggalian: from verse 3 &amp; 5 paratithemai: place beside, entrust, commit, give<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>teknon: child, son proagousas: lead, go before, lead the way, precede<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>propheteias: prophecy strateue: do military service, serve in the army, fight<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>strateian: campaign, warfare kalen: good<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: This command I place beside you, son Timothy, according to the prophecies which went before you, so that you may fight a good fight,</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Pegang karás lu pung parcaya sang Kristus. Deng jaga ko lu pung hati barisi tarús. Te ada orang laen yang su sonde mau dengar dong pung kata hati lai, yang bekin dong pung parcaya ancor, sama ke kapal nae kaná batu karang.<bt>Hold tightly/firmly to your faith/belief in Kristus. And take care that your liver is clean/pure always. Cuz (elaboration) there are other people who aren't willing to listen to their consciences (lit: word/message of liver) anymore, who make their faith/belief broken/smashed, just like a ship that has run aground on a (coral) reef.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kata hati = conscience"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">kata hati = conscience</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="suneigesin: conscience apwsamenoi: reject, not listen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">suneigesin: conscience apwsamenoi: reject, not listen to<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>enauagesan: suffer shipwreck, make a mess, ruin LITERALLY: having faith and a good conscience, which some have rejected, and have shipwrecked their faith;<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Himeneus deng Aleksander dong, parsís ke bagitu su! Andia ko beta su sarakan sang dong pi setan dong pung bos. Beta bekin bagitu, ko biar dong balajar jang bekin rusak Tuhan pung nama lai.<bt>Himeneus and Aleksander are just like that! That is why I have turned them over to the *devil. I did that, so that they learn to not damage God1's name anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***last sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***last sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paredwka: give over, hand over, deliver."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paredwka: give over, hand over, deliver. Also "hand um ova to da Devil" [1 Cor 5:5], but this fits better here. Satanaai: da Devil<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>paideuthwsin: be instructed, be taught, learn blasphemein: blaspheme, slander, speak evil<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: who are Hymenaios and Alexander, whom I have given over to Satan, so that they may learn not to blaspheme.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta bekin bagitu ko ajar sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Beta bekin bagitu ko ajar sang dong barenti bekin rusak Tuhan pung nama.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo orang parcaya dong bakumpul, kotong musti bekin karmana?<bt>When believers gather, how should we-inc do things?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Partama sakali, beta minta bosong sambayang kasi samua orang dong. Kalo bosong mangada sang Tuhan Allah, na, minta ko Dia bantu samua orang yang ada dalam susa. Deng minta tarima kasi, tagal Dia su bekin yang bae kasi dong samua.<bt>First, I ask that you-pl pray for all people. When you-pl face God (=pray), na, ask Him to help all people who are in difficulty. And give thanks, because He has done good (things) for/to all of them. [EXEG: "who are in difficulty" explicating "intercessions"; if stop at "all" redundant with 1st sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakalew: direct, urge, exhort, appeal to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">parakalew: direct, urge, exhort, appeal to prwtos: first<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>poiew: do, make deesis: prayer, supplications, prayer for needs<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>proseuxe: prayer with reverence because of who God is -- current draft emphasizes details too much enteuksis: prayer, intercessions, intercede, request on behalf of others, petition<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>euxaristia: thanksgiving, prayer of thanksgiving huper: concerning, on behalf of, for<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: I direct, therefore, first of all, that requests, prayers, intercessions, and prayers of thanksgiving be made for all people.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Sambayang bagitu ju kasi raja-raja deng samua orang yang ada pegang pimpinan dong. Deng bagitu, kotong samua bisa idop deng tanáng, deng dame, iko Tuhan pung mau, idop yang pantas buat orang yang sémba sang Dia.<bt>Pray like that also for the raja's and all people who are holding leadership. In that way, we-inc can all live in calmness/quietness and peace, according to God1's will, living (in ways that are) appropriate for people who worship Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basileus: king huperoxe: prominence, high position|i(2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">basileus: king huperoxe: prominence, high position<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>eremos: tranquil, quiet, still hesuxeos: quiet, restful, peaceful<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>bios: life, earthly life, physical life diagw: spend one's life, lead one's life, live<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>eusebeia: godliness, religious devotion, piety, duty to God, religion in daily life semnotes: dignity, seriousness, respectfulness, reverence, holiness, gravity, honesty<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: for kings and all who are in high positions, so that we may live a quiet and restful life in all godliness and dignity.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Sambayang macam bagitu tu, bae. Itu bekin sanáng sang Tuhan, yang kasi salamat sang kotong.<bt>Prayers of that sort are good. They please God1, who *saves us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalos: good, morally good, noble, praiseworthy,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kalos: good, morally good, noble, praiseworthy, apodektos: pleasing, acceptable<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>enwpion: before, in the sight of, in the opinion of swter: savior, saving character of<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: This is good and pleasing to our savior God,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dia mau ko samua orang dapa salamat, deng mangarti mana yang batúl. Andia:<bt>He wants all people to get *saved, and to understand what (among choices) is right/correct. That is:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: desire, want something definite, wish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">thelw: desire, want something definite, wish swzw: be saved, be preserved, be delivered<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>epignwsis: knowledge, recognition, realization aletheia: truth, content of Christianity as truth<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>erxomai: come, brought to realization LITERALLY: who desires all people to be saved and to come into the knowledge of truth.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Tuhan Allah tu, satu sa.<bt>That God is just one/there is just one Lord.God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng cuma ada satu jambatan yang bekin dame Tuhan Allah deng kotong manusia, andia Yesus Kristus.<bt>And there is only one bridge/connection which makes peace between God and we-inc humans, that is Yesus Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yesus tu, manusia isi-isi.<bt>And that Yesus, is pure/genuine human. [NOTE: /manusia tulen/ also works, but is identical w/KT for “Son of Man”, so some readers thought it needed to be capitalised, and potentially lose the point of this proposition, so we changed it to /isi-isi/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="juru konci = orang yg pegang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">juru konci = orang yg pegang ko bekin konci ; juru masak ; juru dame ; jambatan = perantara, between fighting parties, untuk orang mau batunangan; tulen = 100%, asli</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mesites: mediator, arbitrator, one who mediates"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">mesites: mediator, arbitrator, one who mediates between two parties to remove a disagreement or reach a common goal, advocate, spokesman between two parties LITERALLY: For there is one God, and one mediator between God and people, the man Christ Jesus,<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Dia sarakan Dia pung diri ko tabús ame kotong samua dari kotong pung sala dong.<bt>He surrendered Himself to redeem/buy.release all of us-inc from our sins/wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabús = pay ransom, redeem, buy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">tabús = pay ransom, redeem, buy freedom or release, UNS says bayar kambali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Pas deng dia pung waktu, ju Tuhan Allah su buka taráng-taráng itu kabar bae ko kasi tau samua orang.<bt>Just at the right time, God openly/clearly revealed that good news to tell all people. [EXEG: NLT; NOTE to daughter translations: consider whether there is a natural way to weave /marturion/ "witness" into the last sentence as a key term; if it is too awkward or forced, unpacking the action/function (as above) is more important than the key term cohesion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV undertranslated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">CEV undertranslated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="didwmi: give antilutros: ransom, redeem, payment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">didwmi: give antilutros: ransom, redeem, payment to free someone. (used only here)<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>marturios: testimony, witness, attested kaipos: time, definite time<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>idios: ones own LITERALLY: who gave himself as a ransom for all, the testimony in his own time;<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang beta jadi Dia pung utusan, ko jalan pi kasi tau orang yang bukan Yahudi dong di mana-mana, deng ajar sang dong ko biar dong ju parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus deng idop iko jalan yang batúl. Apa yang beta kasi tau ni, batúl bagitu. Beta sonde omong kosong.<bt>Then God chose me to be His emmisary/envoy/apostle, to go tell non-Yahudi people everywhere, and teach them so that they also believe in the Lord Yesus and live according to the true/correct way. What I am saying here is true. I am not talking nonsense/B.S. [NOTE to daughter translations: God in first sentence could be pronominalised to He in many languages.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tithemi: make, appoint keruks: herald, preacher,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">tithemi: make, appoint keruks: herald, preacher, announcer, messenger<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>apostolos: apostle, sent with a mission, sent for a purpose aletheia: truth<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>legw: say pseudomai: lie<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>didaskalos: teacher ethnos: nation, people, heathen, pagans, Gentiles<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>pistis: faith, what is believed LITERALLY: for which I was made a preacher and apostle--I speak the truth, I do not lie--a teacher of faith and truth to the nations<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Timotius 1:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta pung mau bagini: di mana-mana, kalo bosong bakumpul ko sambayang, na, bosong musti babae satu deng satu. Jang bamara. Jang bakanjar. Kalo angka tangan waktu sambayang, bosong pung hati musti barisi.<bt>I desire like this: everywhere/wherever, if/when you-pl gather to pray/worship, na, you must be in right relationship with each other.. Don't be angry with each other. Don't be arguing with each other. If/When you lift hands while praying, your-pl livers must be clean/pure. [EXEG: this is /hosios/ not the normal /hagios/. Commentators widely agree that in this verse it is about clean living. All translations, except The Source, keep the figure of hands. DISCOURSE: broad generic principle "right relationships" before specific instances.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***\ov over translated; extensive changes made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***\ov over translated; extensive changes made in discussion with Marge Crofts, Oct. 2005 CEV innocent hands is strange<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boulomai: desire, want, will (more determined"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">boulomai: desire, want, will (more determined than thelw) ; Nyland says the opposite /boulomai/ is less than /thelw/ and can indicate "a mere inclination" (which fits the context of this verse in contrast to vs.4) proseuxomai: pray, public prayer, prayer with reverence<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>andras: man, male (in contrast with "women" in vs. 9) topos: place<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>epairw: lift up, raise, hold up hosios: pious, devout, holy, pleasing to God<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>kheira: hand -- "holy hands" is metonymy; it's holy people, engaging in public prayer using one of the gestures that people used then. The idea is that if they are good people, then praying in public means something; if they aren't good people, then they are just showing off their religion. Focus is on clean lives. (See also Nyland) xwris: apart from, without<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>orge: anger, indignation, wrath dialogismos: dispute, argument, doubt<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: I desire therefore the men should pray in every place, raising holy hands without anger and argument;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta pung mau bagini: Di mana-mana,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Beta pung mau bagini: Di mana-mana, kalo bosong bakumpul ko sambayang, na bosong pung hati musti barisi. Jang bamara. Jang bakanjar. Kalo sambayang, bole angka tangan sang Tuhan Allah ko jadi tanda, bilang, bosong pung hati batúl-batúl barisi.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9-10" />Beta ju mau ko parampuan dong ator diri yang pantas, deng pake pakean yang sopan. Sonde usa bagaya ko bekin orang pasang mata sang dong, deng pake model rambu macam-macam, ko, pake pakean mahal-mahal yang sonde sopan, ko, bastél lebe-lebe pake mas-perak deng mutiara dong. Te yang bekin parampuan dong jadi manis tu, andia dong pung hati yang barisi, deng dong salalu bekin yang bae. Itu yang pantas kasi parampuan yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>I also want women to arrange/organise themselves appropriately, and wear clothes that are decent/respectful/polite. [EXEG: TN] They don't need to show.off.fashion to make people fasten their eyes/pay attention to them [EXEG: NLT], by wearing various hairstyles, or wearing very expensive clothes that are not decent/respectful/polite, or overly dressing themselves up with gold-silver and pearls (=jewelry). Cuz (elaboration) what makes women pretty/attractive, is that their livers are clean/pure [DISCOURSE: from larger context], and they always do what is good. That is what is appropriate for women who worship God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***3rd sentence revised. Don't draw attention"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***3rd sentence revised. Don't draw attention to themselves by x. y. z. [NLT] CHECK revised KM with June aduhai = talalu ; barias = make-up ; hati yang barisi from larger context. ; bagaya<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hwsautws: similarly, likewise, also that, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hwsautws: similarly, likewise, also that, in like manner, in the same way katastole: conduct, behavior, deportment, guise, demeanour<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>kosmios: respectable, honorable, modest, well-ordered, becoming, decorous, appropriate aidws: modesty, self-respect, moral repugnance to what is base and inappropriate, self-restraint, reserve<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>swphrosune: sensibleness, appropriateness, reasonableness, good judgment, moderation, self-control, seriousness, soberness, discretion kosmew: adorn, decorate, dress, arrange<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>plegmasis: entwined, woven, braided xrusiw: gold, gold ornaments, gold jewelry<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>margaritas: pearl, pearl ornament himatismos: clothing, apparel, wardrobe<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>poluteles: costly, expensive LITERALLY: likewise also women should decorate themselves in respectable conduct, with modesty and sensibleness, not with braided hair and gold or pearls or expensive clothing,<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>prepw: befitting, becoming, suitable, appropriate for epaggellomai: profess, proclaim, announce<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>theosebeia: reverence for God, piety, true religion, worship of God ergos: deed, act, accomplishment, work<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>agathos: good LITERALLY: but with good deeds, which is fitting for women who profess reverence for God.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu ju deng parampuan dong. Beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Bagitu ju deng parampuan dong. Beta mau ko dong ator diri yang pantas, deng pake pakean yang sopan. Yang bekin parampuan dong jadi manis batúl tu, bukan tagal dong pung model rambu macam-macam, ko pake pakean mahal-mahal yang sonde sopan, ko bastél lebe-lebe pake mas-perak deng mutiara dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Petrus 3:3</note><v n="11" />Kalo jama'at dong bakumpul ko dengar ajaran, na, parampuan dong ju iko atoran ko pasang talinga bae-bae ko dengar itu ajaran batúl-batúl. Jang bakusu-kusu deng bekin baribut.<bt>[EXEG for passage: vs 11-15 note discussion in Kroeger &amp; Kroeger, 1992; and notes in Nyland 2004]. If/when believers/congregation is gathered to hear teaching, na, women should also follow regulations/guidelines and listen attentively (lit: fasten their ears well) to truly listen to the teaching. [They] shouldn't be whispering to each other and making noise/be noisily disruptive. [EXEG: the obediently/submissively Gk term is seen as “behaviour appropriate to public assembly so all can receive teaching.” following higher level theme.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="the obediently/submissively Gk term is seen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">the obediently/submissively Gk term is seen as "behaviour appropriate to public assembly so all can receive teaching." ; kalam</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hesukhia: silence, quietness, without talking manthanoo:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hesukhia: silence, quietness, without talking manthanoo: learn<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>hupotage: submission, subjection, obedience LITERALLY: Let a woman learn in silence in all submission;<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Iko beta, sonde pantas parampuan angka-angka diri ko maen parenta laki-laki, deng ajar sang dong. Lebe bae parampuan dong tanáng sa.<bt>According to me, it is not appropriate for women to be elevating themselves to order men around, and to teach/correct them. It's better for women to be calm/quiet/composed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde pantas parampuan dong angka-angka diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Sonde pantas parampuan dong angka-angka diri ko parenta laki-laki, ais bekin diri pintar ko ajar sang dong. Lebe bae parampuan dong tanáng sa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="disdaskw: teach epitrepw: permit, allow|i(12) (12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">disdaskw: teach epitrepw: permit, allow<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>authentew: traditionally glossed as "have authority over, domineer, lord it over" (Nyland &amp; others dispute this meaning of this rare word, observing that it NEVER has this meaning (except in the way this verse has been handled traditionally), but means: perpetrator, murderer, author, origin, and originator. Nyland and Kroeger &amp; Kroeger both say this passage is anti-gnostic meaning "I do not permit a woman to teach that man originates from woman, because (vs. 13)) andros: man, male<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: but I do not allow a woman to teach or to have authority over a man, but to be in silence.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te Tuhan Allah bekin sang Adam lebe dolo. Ais itu, baru Hawa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God made Adam first. After that, only then Hawa.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plassw: form, mold, create, make LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">plassw: form, mold, create, make LITERALLY: For Adam was formed first, then Eve.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:7, 2:21-22</note><v n="14" />Deng bukan Adam yang kaná tipu lebe dolo dari setan dong pung bos, ma parampuan. Mulai itu waktu, manusia langgar Tuhan Allah pung atoran.<bt>And it was not Adam who was deceived first from the *devil, but the woman. Beginning from that time, humans violated/contravened God's regulations/guidelines.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apataw: be deceived eksapataw: be thoroughly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">apataw: be deceived eksapataw: be thoroughly deceived<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>parabasis: overstepping, transgressing ginomai: become<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: and Adam was not deceived, but the woman was thoroughly deceived, becoming a transgressor</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:1-6</note><v n="15" />Biar bagitu ju, ma parampuan dong bisa dapa salamat, tagal dong barana ana. Asal dong parcaya batúl sang Kristus, idop basayang, idop deng hati barisi, deng idop pantas.<bt>But even that being the case, women can also be saved, because they give.birth to children. As long as they truly believe in Kristus, live in reciprocal love, live with a clean/pure liver, and live appropriately. [EXEG: Rationale: She blew it for the community of humans by succumbing to sin; but her redemption to the community is through giving life in childbirth, and in living appropriately. The former was a curse, but the latter is a blessing.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***FTN added at Marge Crofts' suggestion,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***FTN added at Marge Crofts' suggestion, Oct. 2005; FTN based on NLT Study Bible plus discussions with Marge. She blew it for the community of humans by succumbing to sin; but her redemption to the community is through giving life in childbirth, and in living appropriately. The former was a curse, but the latter is a blessing.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soozoo: save, preserve tekvogonia: childbirth|i(15) (15)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">soozoo: save, preserve tekvogonia: childbirth<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>menw: remain, stay, continue hagiasmos: holiness, consecration, sanctification, devotion<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>swphrosune: modesty, soberness, good judgment LITERALLY: But they will be saved through childbirth, if they continue in faith and love and holiness with soberness.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab dong bilang ada barapa tafsiran so'al &lt;&lt;parampuan dong bisa dapa salamat, tagal dong barana ana&gt;&gt;. Andia: 1) ada satu Ana, andia Yesus, yang buka jalan ko samua orang bisa dapa salamat; 2) Hawa yang kaná tipu deng bekin sala, ma dia ju jadi nene-moyang kasi samua orang; 3) parampuan yang idop pantas sonde mati waktu barana ana (ma ini tafsiran sonde kuat).<bt>Knowledgeable people about the Bible say there are several interpretations about &lt;&lt;women can also be saved, because they give.birth to children&gt;&gt;. They are: 1) there is one Child, that is Yesus, who opened the way so all people can get saved; 2) Hawa was the one who was tricked and did wrong/sin, but she is also ancestor to all people; 3) women who live appropriately will not die when they give birth (but this interpretation is not strong).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sarat jadi pimpinan jama'at<bt>Requirements/qualifications for becoming a head-leader of a congregation/group of believers</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Memang batúl apa yang orang bilang kata, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau jadi pimpinan jama'at, itu dia pung arti, dia su pili ame satu karjá yang talalu bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>It is true what people say that, &lt;&lt;A person who wants to become head-leader of a congregation, that means, s/he has chosen a very good work.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="syarat ~ sarat = requirement (Ar)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">syarat ~ sarat = requirement (Ar) ; mangga sarat = abundant (fruit), fol-fol, limpah-limpah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistos: trustworthy, sure, certain logos: word,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pistos: trustworthy, sure, certain logos: word, saying<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>episkopos: overseer, bishop oregw: aspire to, strive fo, desire<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>epithumew: desire LITERALLY: This saying is trustworthy: if anyone aspires to be a bishop, he desires a good task.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Pimpinan jama'at dong, musti orang yang pung nama barisi. Dia musti idop satia deng satu bini sa. Dia musti tau tahan diri, kalam, orang hormat sang dia, suka buka pintu ruma ko tarima tamu, deng mampu didik orang laen.<bt>Head-leaders of a congregation must be people who have a clean/pure name/reputation. He must live faithfully with just one wife. he must know how to restrain/control himself, be sensible/stable/not easily upset, people (should) respect him, (he should) enjoy opening the door of his house to receive guests, and be able to teach/educate/mentor other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buka tangan = kebajikan, generous ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">buka tangan = kebajikan, generous ; hati tabuka kasi samua orang = receptive, friendly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pake akal ko timbang bae-bae dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">pake akal ko timbang bae-bae dia pung tindakan,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anepilemptos: irreproachable, above reproach, blameless nephalios:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">anepilemptos: irreproachable, above reproach, blameless nephalios: temperate in the use of wine, sober<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>swphron: prudent, sensible, thoughtful, self-controlled kosmios: respectable, dignified, honorable<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>philoxenos: hospitable, friend of strangers didaktikos: skillful in teaching<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: A bishop must be blameless, the husband of one wife, sober, self-controlled, respectable, hospitable, a good teacher,</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jang orang yang tukang minum mabo, deng jang yang tangan ringan. Yang paling cocok, andia: orang yang hati mas, yang suka cari dame, deng yang sonde rakus doi.<bt>It shouldn't be someone who is a drunkard (&lt; characterised by drinking untill drunk), and shouldn't be someone who is light-handed (Idiom = quick to hit, easily angered and lashes out physically). The best (character) match is someone who has a gold liver (Idiom = gracious), who likes to be a peace-maker, and who is not greedy for money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tangan ringan = gampang pukul orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">tangan ringan = gampang pukul orang ; ringan tangan = rajin ; kode = monyet (maki) ; hati mas = gracious ; manis mulut = tukang putar-balek, janji kosong (kampanye) ; se'ok = pocket some of the money (Rote se'ok = barter, exchange different kinds of goods of equal value</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paroinos: drunken, addicted to wine, alcoholic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paroinos: drunken, addicted to wine, alcoholic plekte: bully, violent, fist-fighter<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>epeieikes: gentle, yielding, kind, mild hamaxos: not quarrelsome, not argumentative<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>aphilarguros: not greedy, not loving money LITERALLY: not drunken, not violent, but gentle, not argumentative, not greedy for money,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dia musti bisa ator dia pung ruma tangga deng bae. Dia pung ana dong musti hormat deng dengar sang dia.<bt>He must be able to manage/organise/regulate/control his own family/household well. His children must respect and listen/obey him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalws: well proistemi: manage, conduct, administer,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kalws: well proistemi: manage, conduct, administer, rule<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>hupotage: submission, subjection, obedience semnotetos: reverence, respectful (translated as if it belonged with hypotageei, but could go with ekhonta).<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: managing his own household well, having children in obedience with all respectfulness;</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Te kalo itu orang sonde bisa ator dia pung ruma tangga sandiri, na, karmana ko dia bisa ator Tuhan pung jama'at?<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if that person can't manage him own household, na, how can he be able to manage God1's congregation/believers?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epimeleomai: care for. LITERALLY: (for if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">epimeleomai: care for. LITERALLY: (for if anyone does not know how to manage his own household, how can he care for the church of God?)<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Lebe bae pili orang yang su dewasa dalam Kristus. Jang angka pimpinan jama'at dari orang yang baru parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Te dong gampang kapala bésar. Jang sampe Tuhan toki sang dia, sama ke Tuhan toki setan dong pung bos.<bt>It is best/better to choose a person who is already mature/adult in Kristus. Don't elevate/install the head-leader of the congregation from people who newly believe in the Lord Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) it's easy for them to become proud/arrogant. One would hope that God1 would not bop him (on the head=judge, punish) like God1 bops the *devil. [NOTE to daughter translations: STYLE: 1st sentence is pos-neg with 2nd sentence to reinforce the point in the way elders do in this region when making a point. Each team can decide whether they prefer it to be in the text or in a footnote.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toki = kadeluk, bop on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">toki = kadeluk, bop on the head ; 04/05 - @@ check if toki is strong enough here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neophutos: recent convert, newcomer tuphow: puffed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">neophutos: recent convert, newcomer tuphow: puffed up, conceited, haughty, arrogant and foolish, proud<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>krima: judgment, condemnation empiptw: fall into<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: not a recent convert, lest he become puffed up and fall into the condemnation of the Devil.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Kalo mau angka orang jadi pimpinan jama'at, na, cari orang yang su ada pung nama bae deng orang luar dong ju. Deng bagitu, dia sonde usa malu apa-apa. Deng setan dong pung bos sonde bisa hiki bekin jato sang dia.<bt>If (you're) going to elevate/appoint a person to be a church leader, na, look for people/a person who already has a good name/reputation with outsiders too. In that way, he doesn't need to be ashamed/embarrassed about anything. And the *devil cannot ensnare him causing him to fall (socially, morally). [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: /Orang luar dong ju musti hormat sang pimpinan jama'at./ “Outsiders must also respect the head-leader of a group of believers (congregation).” BUT check ambiguity that it is not taken as a command for believers to insist unbelievers must show respect to church leaders.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** 1st sentence clarified 2007"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** 1st sentence clarified 2007</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="marturia: testimony, witness kalos: good|i(7) (7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">marturia: testimony, witness kalos: good<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>ekswthen: outside oneidismos: reproach, reviling, disgrace, abuse<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>empiptw: fall pagis: trap, snare<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: But it is necessary for him to have a good testimony from outsiders, so he may not fall into disgrace and the trap of the Devil.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:2-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Titus 1:6-9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang bantu pimpinan jama'at<bt>People who help/assist the head-leader of a congregation</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Bagitu ju deng yang bantu pimpinan jama'at. Dong tu, musti orang yang pung nama bae, yang pung lida sonde bacabang, yang sonde tukang minum mabo, deng jang orang yang suka makan ontong lebe-lebe.<bt>It is the same way also for those who help/assist the head-leader of a congregation. They must/should be people of good name/reputation, who are not hypocrites (lit: don't have branching tongues), who are not drunks, and they shouldn't be people who like excessive (or dishonest) gain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lida sonde bacabang = omong laen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">lida sonde bacabang = omong laen di sini, laen di sana, consistent, pendirian kuat ; muka dua = omong balakang bilang laen, muka bilang laen ; makan ontong = two understandings 1) excessive, or dishonest gain, 2) any profit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: Use this as the model"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">TERM: Use this as the model for the parallel part of Titus (1:6-7) diakonos: deacon as a subordinate officer of the church, servant, minister, servant in a menial capacity, servant who sacrifices himself<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>semnos: serious, dignified, noble, person worthy of respect, worthy, soberminded. Titus 1:7 and 1 Tim 2:2 are the model for this. dilogos: double-tongued, insincere, not straightforward, not truthful, hypocritical, deceitful<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>prosexw: addicted, occupy oneself with, devoted to aisxrokerdeis: greedy for dishonest gain, moneygrubbing<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: Deacons likewise serious, not insincere, not addicted to much wine, not greedy for dishonest gain,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Dong pung hati musti barisi, deng dong musti pegang karás ajaran yang Tuhan su buka kasi tunju sang kotong orang parcaya dong.<bt>Their livers must be clean/pure, and they must hold strongly to the teaching which the God1 has revealed to us-inc, believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="musterion: mystery, secret, secret rite, secret"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">musterion: mystery, secret, secret rite, secret teaching, hidden thing katharos: clear, pure<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>suneidesis: conscience, moral consciousness LITERALLY: holding the mystery of the faith with a good conscience.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Pareksa bae-bae dong pung idop deng dong pung karjá. Kalo orang sonde dapa dong pung sala, baru angka sang dong ko bantu pimpinan jama'at dong.<bt>Carefully investigate/examine their life and their work. If nobody finds their fault/wrong/sin, only then elevate/install them to assist the head-leaders of the congregation/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimazw: put to the test, test,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">dokimazw: put to the test, test, examine eita: then<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>diakoneitw: serve as a deacon anegkletos: blameless, irreproachable, guiltless, without stain<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: But let them be tested first, then if they are blameless, let them serve as a deacon.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Bagitu ju deng dong pung bini.<bt>The same also with their wives.</bt><note reference="3:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata bahasa Yunani di sini γυναῖκας <span class="Italic">(gunaikas</span> dari kata dasar γυνή <span class="Italic">(gunē)),</span> dia pung arti bisa 1) &lt;&lt;dong pung bini&gt;&gt;, ko bisa ju 2) &lt;&lt;parampuan&gt;&gt; (umum). Ada orang saparu bilang, itu kata pung maksud di sini ju bisa 3) parampuan yang bantu pimpin jama'at. Ma kalo yang katiga, bahasa Yunani biasa pake kata laen (lia <span class="Italic">Roma</span> 16:1).<bt>The Yunani language word here γυναῖκας <span class="Italic">(gunaikas </span>from the root γυνή <span class="Italic">(gunē)),</span> its meaning can be 1) &lt;&lt;their wives&gt;&gt;, or it can also be 2) &lt;&lt;women&gt;&gt; (in general). There are some people who say this word's intent here can also be 3) women who assist leading he congregation. But if it's the third, the Yunani language normally uses a different word (see Roma 16:1).</bt></note>Dong tu, musti parampuan yang idop pantas deng bae-bae. Jang yang tukang bekin busuk orang laen pung nama. Dong musti tau tahan diri, deng orang ju bisa parcaya sang dong.<bt>They should be women who lives appropriately and well/good. They should not be people characterised by making other people's name rotten. They must know how to restrain/control themselves, and people must be able to trust them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added FTN"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***added FTN</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diabolos: slanderous nephalios: temperate, sober. TERM,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">diabolos: slanderous nephalios: temperate, sober. TERM, also in 3:2.<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: Wives/women likewise serious, not slanderous, temperate, faithful in everything.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Yang bantu pimpinan jama'at dong ju musti laki yang satia deng satu bini sa. Dia ju musti tau ator dia pung ruma tangga deng bae, deng musti tau ator dia pung ana-ana dong.<bt>Those who help/assist the head-leaders of congregation/s must also be men who are loyal/faithful to just one wife. He must know how to manage his household well, and must know how to manage his children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proistemi: manage, lead LITERALLY: Let deacons"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">proistemi: manage, lead LITERALLY: Let deacons be the husband of one wife, managing their children and their own household well;<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dong yang ada layani jama'at deng bae, pasti orang tamba hormat sang dong. Deng dong tamba barani, sonde taku omong so'al dong pung parcaya sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>Those who are serving congregations well, surely people will respect them even more. And they will increase in boldness, and not be afraid to speak because of their faith in the Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bathmos: step, grade, rank, standing, status"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">bathmos: step, grade, rank, standing, status peripoiew: gain, acquire, obtain<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: For those who serve well as deacons win for themselves a good status and much boldness in the faith in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dasar dari kotong pung parcaya<bt>The basis of our-inc faith/belief</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14-15" />Tius! Beta harap sonde lama lai, beta su bisa datang lia sang lu. Andekata beta ada halangan, ko, datang talát, na, ini surat su sampe lebe dolo di lu pung tangan. Beta tulis ini surat ko mau kasi tau sang lu bilang, Tuhan pung kelu dong musti idop karmana. Jang lupa bilang, Tuhan tu, Allah yang idop. Dia pung orang dong sama ke ruma yang ada pung dasar deng tiang induk yang kuat. Deng bagitu, dong musti topang Tuhan Allah pung ajaran yang batúl.<bt>Tius (Tim)! I hope that I will soon be able to come and see you-sg. If, perchance, I get an obstacle or arrive late, na, this letter has reached your hand first. I write this so I can tell you how God1's kin/family should live. Don't forget that God1 is the God2 who lives. His people (collectively) are like a house which has a strong foundation/base and main post. In that way they must support/prop up God's true/correct teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I write you these things,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I write you these things, hoping to come to you soon; bradunw: delay, hesitate<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>anastrephw: to behave, act, live LITERALLY: But if I delay, so that you may know how it is necessary to behave in the household of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and foundation of the truth.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Tuhan su buka rahasia yang hebat dari kotong pung parcaya. Dia pung dasar bagini:<bt>God1 has already revealed the great secret of our-inc faith/belief. It's basis/foundation is like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** first line of explicating Kristus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** first line of explicating Kristus not necessary as redundant and skewing focus--deleted (Marge Crofts, Oct. 2005); several codes reformatted in this section</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus tu, orang yang Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Kristus tu, orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kristus su datang di ini dunya,<bt>Kristus has come into this world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pake manusia pung rupa sama ke kotong.<bt>using human's form/face like/similar to us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***delete connector"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***delete connector</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan pung Roh ju kasi tunju bilang,<bt>God1's Spirit is also showed/demonstrated that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yesus tu, Orang hati lurus.<bt>Yesus [+known ref] is a straight livered (righteous/just) Person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added /ju/ and changed object of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***added /ju/ and changed object of CEV is wierd here;<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Tuhan pung ana bua di sorga dong ju dapa lia sang Dia.<bt>And God1's *angels in heaven were also able to see Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan Allah su angka ame sang Dia pi dalam sorga,<bt>God has taken Him up/elevated Him into *heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais angka nae tinggi-tinggi sang Dia.<bt>and then glorified/elevated/exalted Him. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** changed order to more chronological,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** changed order to more chronological, TN</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pung Carita su tasiar sampe di suku-bangsa di anteru dunya.<bt>His Story, has spread to reaching the various ethnic groups/races throughout the world.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Di mana-mana di ini dunya, orang dong su parcaya sang Dia.<bt>Everywhere in this world, people already believe in Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kotong pung parcaya bagitu!<bt>That's what we-inc believe!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homologein: to confess, to acknowledge mega:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">homologein: to confess, to acknowledge mega: great<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>eusebeias: godliness musterion: mystery<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>phanerew: appear sarks: flesh, body<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>dikaiow: justify, vindicate, proven to be right, shown to be right, validated, verified, put right with, acquitted, set free, show justice to s.o., consider correct, acknowledge validity of analambanw: taken up<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: And we confess, great is the mystery of godliness; Who was shown in the flesh, Justified in [the] spirit, Seen by angels, Preached among the nations, Believed on by the world, Taken up in glory.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ati-ati deng orang yang ajar harba-biruk kasi jama'at dong<bt>Be careful with people who teach chaotically (=outside of ordered norms) to the believers/congregations</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ma Tuhan pung Roh su kasi tau taráng-taráng bilang, nanti jama'at saparu tola buang apa yang kotong parcaya. Ais dong pi iko roh-roh yang tipu bekin sesát manusia, deng iko setan dong pung ajaran.<bt>But God1's Spirit has made known very clearly that later some believers will reject/throw away what we-inc believe. So they will go off and follow/obey spirits which deceive making humans lost, and follow the teaching of demons. [EXEG: ‘now’ in interlinear is Gk /de/. It is a discourse marker, not a time word meaning ‘now’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="luntur = fade ; sesat ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">luntur = fade ; sesat = lost</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneuma: spirit hretos: expressly, explicitly, specifically|i(1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pneuma: spirit hretos: expressly, explicitly, specifically<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>legw: say husteros: latter, later, last<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kairos: time aphistemi: fall away, depart, remove themselves<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>pistis: faith, what is believed prosexw: pay attention to, give heed to, follow<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>planos: deceitful, seductive didaskalia: teaching, doctrine<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>daimonion: demon, evil spirit LITERALLY: But the Spirit says specifically that in later times certain ones will depart from the faith, paying attention to deceitful spirits and teachings of demons,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Itu orang yang datang ajar bagitu tu, omong laen, bekin laen. Dasar orang putar-balek! Itu orang dong pung hati nurani memang su buta.<bt>Those people who come teaching like that, they say one thing and do another. They are fundamentally deceivers/cheaters/swindlers! [DISCOURSE: Worded like a curse or strong condemnation]. Their consciences are blind/dull.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="munafik = hypocrite ; kalap ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">munafik = hypocrite ; kalap = lawan dari kalam, panic ; mata hati = nurani ; hati nurani = conscience (BI?) ; hati kici 1) hati nurani, 2) penakut (kecil hati)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupokrisis: hypocrisy, pretense, outward show pseudologos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hupokrisis: hypocrisy, pretense, outward show pseudologos: liar, false speaker<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>kausteriazw: sear, cauterize, burn into insensitivity idios: one's own<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>suneidesis: conscience, moral consciousness LITERALLY: in hypocrisy of liars, having their own consciences seared,<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Dong ajar orang ko jang kawin. Dong bekin pamali macam-macam makanan. Padahal Tuhan Allah yang bekin itu makanan dong. Dia bekin itu makanan dong, ko kalo orang parcaya dong makan, na, dong minta tarima kasi sang Dia. Te dong tau apa yang batúl na!<bt>They teach people to not marry. They make taboo various sorts of food. Whereas in fact God is the one who made those foods. He made those foods so that when believers eat, na, they give thanks to Him. Cuz (elaboration) they know what's right/true/correct (+certainly)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Restructured to add purpose"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** Restructured to add purpose</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kwluw: hinder, forbid, prohibit gamew: marry|i(3)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kwluw: hinder, forbid, prohibit gamew: marry<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>apexw: keep away, abstain brwma: food<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>ktizw: create metalempsis: receive<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>euxaristia: thanksgiving pistis: faith, belief<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>epiginwskw: know aletheia: truth<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: forbidding to marry, keeping away from foods which God created for receiving with thanksgiving by those who believe and know the truth.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong ajar orang ko jang kawin."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Dong ajar orang ko jang kawin. Dong bekin pamali macam-macam makanan. Padahal Tuhan Allah yang bekin itu makanan dong. Jadi, kalo orang parcaya dong makan, na, dong minta tarima kasi sang Dia. Dong tau apa yang batúl!</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Samua yang Tuhan Allah bekin tu, memang bae. Jadi jang pamali macam-macam! Orang musti tarima itu samua deng minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Everything that God has done/made, is truly good. So (consequently), don't make taboos trivially/excessively/pointlessly! People should accept all of it and give thanks to God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pamali = vt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">pamali = vt</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pas: all, everything ktisma: creation, creature|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pas: all, everything ktisma: creation, creature<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>kalos: good apobletos: rejected, refused, thrown away, taboo<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>lambanw: receive, take, grasp, take hold of, get, obtain LITERALLY: Because every creation of God is good, and nothing to be rejected if it is received with thanksgiving,<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Te kotong tau bilang, Tuhan pung Kata-kata, deng kotong pung sambayang, bekin itu samua jadi barisi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-inc know that God1's Words, and our-inc prayers, make all of those things to be/become clean/pure.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagiazw: sanctify, consecrate, dedicate, set apart"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hagiazw: sanctify, consecrate, dedicate, set apart fo God, make holy logos: word<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>enteuksews: prayer LITERALLY: for it is sanctified through the word of God and prayer.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung orang karjá yang bae<bt>A good worker of the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tius! Kasi inga ini hal samua sang sodara orang parcaya dong. Kalo lu bekin bagitu, lu jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang karjá yang bae. Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata dong bekin lu parcaya sang Dia, deng kasi mangarti mana ajaran yang batúl. Lu su pegang kuat Tuhan pung Kata-kata dong. Itu sama ke makanan yang bekin kuat lu pung badan.<bt>Tius (Tim)! Remind our brother-sister believers of all these things. If/when you-sg do that, you are a good worker of Yesus Kristus. God's Words made/makes you (to) believe in Him, and made/allowed you to understand which teachings are true/correct. You have been holding firmly to God1's Words. They are just like food that gives strength to your body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupotithemi: suggest, point out something, make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hupotithemi: suggest, point out something, make known, show, remind adelphos: brother<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>kalos: good diakonos: servant, minister, helper<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>entrephw: bring up, nourish, rear as a child, train logos: word<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>pistis: faith didaskalia: teaching<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>parakolouthew: follow, attend to a course of instruction LITERALLY: Reminding the brothers of these things, you will be a good servant of Christ Jesus, being nourished by the words of faith, an of the good teaching which you have followed;<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jang buang-buang waktu deng carita omong kosong yang sonde ada pung hubungan deng Tuhan Allah. Jang toe deng nene tua dong pung carita pamali macam-macam. Lebe bae lati bae-bae lu pung diri ko biar lu idop iko Tuhan pung mau dalam samua hal.<bt>Don't waste time with pointless stories that have no connection with God. Don't pay any attention to the old grandmas tales explaining various taboos. It is better for you to train yourself well/carefully so that you live according to God1's will in all matters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lebe bae lati lu pung diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Lebe bae lati lu pung diri ko biar lu pung parcaya tamba kuat.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bebelos: profane, godless grawdes: like an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">bebelos: profane, godless grawdes: like an old woman, silly, foolish, frivolous, absurd, senseless<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>muthos: fable, myth, tale, story, legend paraiteomai: refuse, reject, avoid, have nothing to do with<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>gumnazw: train, exercise seautos: yourself<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>eusebeia: godliness, religion, piety LITERALLY: but refuse godless and silly stories, and train yourself in godliness;<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Lati diri ko bekin kuat badan tu, bae.<bt>Training yourself to strengthen your body is good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma dia pung guna sadiki sa.<bt>But it is only useful a little bit.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma lati diri ko idop iko Tuhan pung mau dalam samua hal tu,<bt>But training yourself to live according to God1's will in all matters,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dia pung guna banya.<bt>it has many uses/is useful for many things.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ada pung guna<bt>It is useful</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bukan cuma dalam idop di ini dunya sakarang sa,<bt>not only for life in this world now,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ma di idop yang nanti datang ju.<bt>but also for life that is coming later.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="swmatikos: bodily gumnasia: training, exercise|i(8) (8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">swmatikos: bodily gumnasia: training, exercise<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>oligos: little, a little, some wphelimos: useful, beneficial, advantageous<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>eusebeia: godliness, piety, religion epaggelia: promise, offer, pledge<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>exw: have zwe: life<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>nun: now, present mellw: to be destined, to come<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: for bodily exercise is profitable for a little, butt godliness is profitable for all things, having promise of life now and to come.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ini kata-kata dong batúl! Jadi simpan dalam hati ko jang lupa.<bt>These words are true/correct! So (consequently) store/save/place them away in your liver so you don't forget.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistos: faith, faithful, trustworthy, sure logos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pistos: faith, faithful, trustworthy, sure logos: word, saying<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>pas: all, full apodoxes: acceptance, approval<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>aksios: worthy, deserving LITERALLY: The saying is trustworthy and deserving of full acceptance;<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kotong ada taro harap sang Tuhan Allah yang idop. Dia yang kasi salamat samua orang, lebe-lebe kasi kotong yang parcaya sang Dia. Andia ko kotong ada karjá karás deng usaha mati-matian.<bt>[EXEG: he is Saviour of all, but even in 1 Tim, that does not mean that all are saved. so Saviour of all is taken in the weak sense, not the strong sense] We-inc are placing our hope in God who lives. He is the one who gives (~makes available) salvation to everyone, especially those of us-inc who believe in Him. That is why we-inc are working hard and striving/making every effort [+extreme degree].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taro1 = put, place ; taro2"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">taro1 = put, place ; taro2 = pukul, ajar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kopiaw: toil, become weary, labor, work"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kopiaw: toil, become weary, labor, work hard agwnizomai: struggle, strive, fight<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>elpizw: hope zaw: live<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>swter: savior malista: above all, especially<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>pistos: faith LITERALLY: toward which we work hard and struggle, because we hope on the living God, who is the savior of all men, especially of the ones that believe.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ajar ini samua. Deng suru orang dong ko iko itu ajaran dong.<bt>Teach all this/these things. And order/tell people to follow/obey these teachings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraggellw: give orders, command didaskw: teach|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paraggellw: give orders, command didaskw: teach<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: Command and teach these things.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Jang kasi biar orang dong pandang enteng sang lu tagal lu masi muda. Lu musti jadi conto kasi orang parcaya dong, dari lu pung omong, lu pung tingka-laku, lu pung cara sayang orang, lu pung parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, deng lu pung idop yang barisi.<bt>Don't let people to look down on/scorn/disparage you because you are still young. You-sg must be an example for the believers, from what you say, your behaviour, the way you love people, your faith/belief in Yesus Kristus, and your clean/pure life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="medeis: no veotes: youth|i(12) (12) |rkataphronew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">medeis: no veotes: youth<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kataphronew: scorn, despise tupos: mark, example, pattern<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>ginomai: become, be pistos: trustworthy<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>logos: word, speech anastpophhe: conduct, way of life<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>agape: love pistis: faith, trust, confidence<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>hagneia: purity, moral cleanness LITERALLY: Don't let anyone scorn your youth, but be a model for those who believe in word, in conduct, in love, in faith, in purity.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Waktu bosong ada tunggu beta pung datang, na, jang lupa ko baca Tuhan pung Kata-kata kasi orang parcaya dong. Kasi kuat sang dong, deng ajar bae-bae sang dong.<bt>While you-pl are waiting for my coming, don't forget to read God1's Words to the believers. Strengthen/ encourage them, and teach them well. [EXEG: NLT, LN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hews: until erxomai: come|i(13) (13) |rprosexw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hews: until erxomai: come<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>prosexw: pay attention to, devote yourself to, occupy yourself with anagnwsis: reading, public reading<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>paraklesis: encouragement, exhortation, preaching didaskalia: teaching, doctrine<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: Until I come pay attention to the public reading, to preaching, to the teaching.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Pake bae-bae karunya yang Tuhan su kasi sang lu, yang lu tarima waktu pimpinan jama'at dong sambayang deng taro tangan di lu. Itu waktu, dong ju ada kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán so'al lu pung idop deng karjá. Jadi jang kasi biar itu karunya yang lu su dapa.<bt>Use well the *gift/ability.from.above (karunya) which God1 has given you-sg, which you received when the leaders of the congregation/believers prayed and placed their hands on your head. At that time, they also made known God1's message/instructions about your life and work. So (consequently), don't let it lie the gift that you have. [DISCOURSE: Reinforce main point and get application from the negative.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pesán = message, instructions ; @@"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">pesán = message, instructions ; @@ delete kapala July 2005 ***Last sent added to reinforce and get application from the negative</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="amelew: neglect, leave, lack of attention"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">amelew: neglect, leave, lack of attention xarisma: a gift<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>didwmi: give propheteia: prophecy<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>epithesis: laying on xeirwn: hand<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>presbuterion: council of elders LITERALLY: Do not neglect the gift in you, which was given you through prophecy with the laying on of hands by the elders.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kasi jalan itu hal dong deng rajin! Biar samua orang dapa lia bilang, lu pung idop deng karjá ada maju.<bt>Carry out those matters with diligence/ industriousness! Let everyone see that your life and work are making progress/moving forward.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meletaw: practise eimi: be|i(15) (15) |rprokope:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">meletaw: practise eimi: be<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>prokope: progress phaneros: clear<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>pas: all LITERALLY: Practise these things, give yourself to them, that your progress may be seen by everyone.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Andia: jaga ko lu salalu idop lurus. Deng jaga ko lu salalu ajar yang batúl. Kalo lu bakuat deng itu samua, nanti Tuhan buka jalan kasi lu deng orang-orang yang dengar sang lu, ko biar bosong talapás dari hal yang jahat dong.<bt>That is: take care that you-sg always live straight/righteous/just. And take care that you always teach what is right/correct. If/when you are strong/persevere with all that, then God1 will open the way for you and the people who listen to you, so that you-pl can be freed/released/spared from evil/bad things. [EXEG: (Key Term): HCE: while Knight and others argue for a "soterilogical (spiritual) salvation" here, TN and TH discuss significant complexities/problems with that, and TH gives an alternate translation similar to above. Carlton also adds object to "saved (from eternal destruction)". The complications with going literal for Kupang and surrounding lgs is 1) it implies Timothy is not yet saved (addressed at length in TN, but without saying how to handle it, and still a problem for KM), and 2) saying that Timothy can save himself (which the Gk does say, but it creates significant worldview/lexical clashes here (similar to a human cannot "bless" God). So here, to not introduce error and misunderstandings, we have had to go Specific -- Generic, using /swzw/ meaning of "preserve, keep from harm" (LN, BAGD), which is adequate for the context and much less problematic for KM.] [NOTE to daughter translations: /Kalo lu bakuat deng itu samua/ If unclear/unhelpful, try /Kalo lu idop bagitu.../]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***see added notes above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***see added notes above</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epexw: aim at, pay attention to,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">epexw: aim at, pay attention to, keep a close watch on, hold to seautou: yourself<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>didaskalia: teaching, doctrine epimenw: continue, remain, persist, stick to, cling to<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>poiew: do swzw: save, rescue (from danger, destruction), preserve, keep from harm<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>akouw: hear LITERALLY: Keep a close watch on yourself and the teaching; continue in them; for by doing this you will save yourself and those who hear you.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Timotius pung sikap kasi jama'at dong<bt>Timotius' attitude/demeanor toward the believers/congregation</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Jang togor orang yang lebe tua dari lu, pake suara karás. Ma pake bahasa yang manis, sama ke lu omong deng lu pung bapa sandiri. Deng orang yang lebe muda, na, kasi samangat sang dong, sama ke dong tu, lu pung sodara sandiri.<bt>Don't scold/reprimand people who are older than you-sg using a loud/harsh voice. But use language that is sweet (=polite, attractive, positive), just like you would use with your own father. And with people who are younger, na, encourage/inspire/enthuse them, just as if they are your own sibling.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="presbuteros: elder, older man epiplessw: rebuke,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">presbuteros: elder, older man epiplessw: rebuke, reprove, scold, bawl out, strike at (strong)<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>parakalew: exhort, appeal to, urge, encourage, console, conciliate, speak to in a friendly manner, admonish, comfort, call aside newteros: younger man<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Do not scold an older man, but appeal to him as a father, young men as brothers,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Bagitu ju deng parampuan yang lebe tua dong. Omong deng dong sama ke lu omong deng lu pung mama sandiri. Kalo omong deng parampuan yang lebe muda dong, na, anggap dong sama ke lu pung adi sandiri. Lu pung hati musti barisi deng dong.<bt>It is the same with women who are older. Speak to them just as you would speak to your own mother. If you speak with women who are younger, na, consider them just like your own younger sister. Your liver must be clean/pure with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagneia: purity, moral purity, chastity, blamelessness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hagneia: purity, moral purity, chastity, blamelessness LITERALLY: older women as mothers, younger women as sisters in all purity.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al janda dong<bt>About/concerning widows</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3-5" />Jama'at musti bantu mama-mama janda, yang sonde ada pung kelu yang piara sang dong lai. Ma kalo janda yang masi ada pung ana-cucu, na, dong tu yang musti piara sang dia. Ajar sang dong, ko dong tau balas dia pung karingat sang dong. Deng bagitu dong layani sang Tuhan Allah, ko bekin sanáng Dia pung hati. Ma janda yang batúl-batúl idop sandiri, dia su sonde ada sapa-sapa lai ko piara sang dia. Dia cuma harap sang Tuhan Allah sa. Siang-malam dia sambayang minta tolong sang Tuhan Allah. Jama'at musti piara sang janda macam bagitu dong.<bt>The congregation/believers must help/assist widow ladies, who don't have any family/kin who can take care of them any more. But as for widows who still have children-grandchildren, na, they are the ones who must take care of her. Teach them, so they know/are able to repay/reciprocate her sweat (=effort) to them. In that way they serve God, to please His liver. But (as for) widows who truly live alone, she doesn't have anyone else to take care of her. She only hopes in God alone. Day-night (=constantly) she prays asking for help from God. The believers/congregations must/should take care of widows of that sort.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balas budi = repay jasa (BI)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">balas budi = repay jasa (BI) ; balas bae ; balas karingat ; bayar aer susu = (at wedding negotiations) ; pukul susu = sumpah, kutuk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xeras: widow timaw: honor, revere, respect,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">xeras: widow timaw: honor, revere, respect, material support<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: Honor widows that are really widows. teknon: child<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>ekgonos: grandchild manthanw: learn<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>prwton: first oikos: household, family<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>eusebew: be reverent, respectful, honor, devout, pious, religious duty amoibas: return, repayment<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>apodidomi: reward, make a return, repay progonos: parent<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>apodektos: acceptable, pleasing LITERALLY: But if any widow has children or grandchildren, let them learn first to show godly honor to their own family and repay their parents, for this is pleasing before God.<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>monow: be left alone, solitary elpizw: set hope on<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>prosmenw: continue deesis: prayer, entreaty, pleading, request<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>proseuxe: general prayer LITERALLY: But the widow who is alone sets her hope on God, and continues in requests and prayers night and day;<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma janda yang suka idop sanáng-sanáng sa, biar dia masi idop, ma dia su sonde ada pung harga lai, sama ke orang yang su mati.<bt>But (as for) widows who just like to live happily (=lazy, or for their own pleasure), even though she still lives, she nevertheless has no more worth/use/value, like a person who has already died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added last clause to restore image"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***added last clause to restore image</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="spatalaw: live luxuriously or voluptuously, indulge,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">spatalaw: live luxuriously or voluptuously, indulge, give self to pleasure, indulge freely in eating and drinking, yield to the appetites zaw: live<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>thneskw: die LITERALLY: But the one who gives herself to pleasure is dead while she is living.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Kasi inga itu hal samua sang jama'at, ko biar orang luar sonde bisa omong bekin rusak dong pung nama bae.<bt>Remind the believers/congregation of all these things, so that outsiders cannot speak causing damage to their good name/reputation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraggellw: command, direct, urge, insist on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paraggellw: command, direct, urge, insist on anepilemptos: be without reproach, irreproachable, blameless<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Command these things, so that they may be blameless.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma kalo ada orang yang sonde mau piara dia pung kelu sandiri, lebe-lebe dia pung isi ruma sandiri, itu sama ke dia su angka buang dia pung parcaya sang Tuhan. Dia lebe jahat dari orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>But if there are people who don't want to take care of their own family/kin, especially (from) his/her own family members, that is just like s/he has thrown away/discarded his/her faith/belief in God1. S/he is more evil than people who don't know/recognise God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pronoew: think of beforehand, take care,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">pronoew: think of beforehand, take care, provide arneomai: deny, repudiate, disown<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>apistos: faithless, unbelieving xeipwn: worse<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: But if anyone does not provide for his own, and especially his own household, he has denied the faith and is worse than an unbeliever.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Kalo mau angka janda ko bantu pimpinan di jama'at, dia pung sarat bagini: dia pung umur sonde bole kurang dari 60 taon; dolu dia idop satia deng satu laki sa;<bt>If you want to elevate/appoint/install a widow to assist/help the leaders of the congregation, the requirements/qualifications are like this: her age shouldn't be below 60 years old; formerly she should have lived faithfully/loyally with just one husband; [EXEG: Exegetical choice 1) “list for support” as TEV, Trans. Hand., NLT, sets up many contextual and practical problems, or 2) those designated for holding some sort of leadership responsibilities. The Kupang team takes two. See reference to “promise” in v.12, and parallels of qualifications for deacons as support. Higher level context &amp; book themes.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katalegw: select, enroll elatton: less|i(9) (9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">katalegw: select, enroll elatton: less<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>etos: year heksekonta: sixty<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>gune: heis: one<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: Enroll widows not less than sixty years old, the wife of one husband,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />orang kanál sang dia salaku orang yang salalu bekin bae kasi orang laen; yang piara dia pung ana-ana deng bae-bae; yang buka tangan ko layani orang laen; yang bantu-bantu orang parcaya deng karjá yang kici-kici dong; yang suka bantu orang yang ada dalam susa; deng yang salalu siap ko bantu-bantu dalam hal yang bae.<bt>people know/recognise her as a person who always does good things to/for other people; as one who took good care of her own children; as one who opened her hands (=willingly) to serve other people; as one who makes herself useful/does whatever is need to help (Idiom: help-help) the believers in even the small/unimportant things; as one who likes to/often help people who are in difficulty; and as one who is always ready to do whatever is needed to help with good/worthy things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bantu-bantu = do whatever is needed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">bantu-bantu = do whatever is needed, making self useful</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="marturew: be well spoken of, testified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">marturew: be well spoken of, testified about teknotrophew: nourishing children, bring up children<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>ksenodoxew: show hospitality to strangers thlibw: oppress, afflict<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>eparkew: help, relieve, aid hagios: saints<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>pous foot niptw: wash<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>epakolouthew: follow after, devote self to LITERALLY: having a testimony of good works, if she has brought up children, if she has been hospitable to strangers, if she has washed the feet of the saints, if she has helped the troubled, if she has devoted herself to every good work.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Jang angka janda muda dong ko bantu di jama'at. Te jang sampe dong pung nafsu nae datang, ju dong kapingin kawin lai. Deng bagitu, dong su sonde ada pung waktu lai ko layani jama'at deng bae-bae.<bt>Don't elevate/appoint young widows to help in the congregation. Cuz (elaboration) it wouldn't be good if (lit: it should not be to the point that) their passion/lust arises, and they want to get married again. In that way, they don't have any more time to serve the congregation well. [EXEG: last sentence covers “against Christ”. Problem: if say “serve Christ's people” it's a bit narrow, leaving out “Christ's work”. And bridges into vs. 12.] [NOTE to daughter translations: “nafsu” is a problem in most vernaculars. ALT: “May it not be that their desire to marry again, pushes out of the way their thinking about/attention to Kristus.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nafsu nae datang ; berahi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">nafsu nae datang ; berahi = nafsu sexual ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraitew: refuse katastreniazw: [young ox] trying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paraitew: refuse katastreniazw: [young ox] trying to escape from the yoke, exercise youthful vigor against, be restless against, resist<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: But refuse to enroll younger widows, for whenever they exercise youthful vigor against Christ, they desire to marry,</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Te kalo dong pung waktu kasi jama'at kurang, itu sama sa deng dong bekin rusak dong pung janji di Tuhan pung muka. Nanti orang kasi sala sang dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if/when their time available to the congregation/believers diminishes, that is the same as if they have broken their promise before God1. Then people will blame/accuse them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="janji = refers back to installation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">janji = refers back to installation in v.9?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="atheteo: declare invalid, nullify, set aside,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">atheteo: declare invalid, nullify, set aside, break a pledge LITERALLY: bringing condemnation on themselves because they have set aside their first promise<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Jang sampe dong mulai pamalas, ais batasibu pi maso-kaluar orang dong pung ruma, ko bacarita omong kosong bekin rusak orang pung nama. Deng yang lebe rotsoi lai, dong suka batasosok deng orang laen pung parkara, deng omong hal-hal yang sonde pantas.<bt>It would not be good if they began to be lazy, and then busy themselves going in-out of people's houses, to tell foolish/nonsense/pointless tales [that] damage people's name/reputation. And what is even worse, they [would] like/tend to butt in/involve themselves in other people's matters/disputes, and say things that are not appropriate.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rotsoi = Belanda jahat, parah, rusak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">rotsoi = Belanda jahat, parah, rusak ; soi = sial</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hama: together argos: idle|i(13) (13) |rmanthanw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hama: together argos: idle<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>manthanw: learn perierxomai: go around<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>phluaros: gossipy periergos: meddlesome<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>lalew: speak dei: it is necessary<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: Besides, they learn to be lazy, going around the houses, and not only lazy, but gossipy and meddlesome, talking about what they shouldn't.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ada lebe bae, janda yang masi muda dong kawin ulang sa, ko biar dong barana, deng urus dong pung ruma tangga sandiri. Deng bagitu, orang yang musu sang kotong sonde dapa alasan ko bekin busuk kotong pung nama.<bt>It would be better for widows who are still young to just marry again, so they can have children (lit. give birth), and manage their own household. In that way, people who are hostile to us-inc have no reason/excuse to make rotten our-inc name/reputation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boulomai: desire tekvogonew: bear children|i(14) (14)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">boulomai: desire tekvogonew: bear children<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>oikodespotew: manage household medeis: no<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>aphorme: pretext, reason antikeimai: be opposed, oppose. Could refer to the Devil, or to any opponent<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>loidoria: abuse, revile xarin: for the sake of, on account of, because of<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: I desire therefore younger widows to marry, to bear children, to manage their households, to not give the opponent a reason to revile;</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ada janda muda saparu yang su sesát. Dong su iko setan dong pung bos pung jalan.<bt>There are some young widows who have already lost their way. They are following/obeying the way/path of the *devil.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ektrepw: turn away, turn, stray, swerve"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">ektrepw: turn away, turn, stray, swerve opisw: after<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>Satanaa: da Devil LITERALLY: for already some have turned away after Satan.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kalo ada parampuan yang parcaya sang Tuhan, yang ada pung kelu su jadi janda, na, itu parampuan musti bantu itu mama janda. Jang kasi biar jama'at yang tanggong sang dia. Deng bagitu, jama'at dong bisa bantu janda laen dong, yang memang su sonde ada pung sapa-sapa lai.<bt>If there is a woman who belives in the Lord, whose family/kin has become a widow, na, that woman must help/assist that mama widow. Don't let/allow the congregation to carry the responsibility for her livlihood. In that way, the congregation can help other widows, who really have nobody else. [EXEG: / TEXT: TB has “believing man or woman” following a textual variant with less support. AGNT, context, NRSV, NLT, CEV, NIV all favour “woman”.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if RL has to specify Tuhan as God or Jesus, go with Jesus see TH).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kans = kesempatan (June doesn't have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">kans = kesempatan (June doesn't have in active vocabulary)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eparkeitw: help, aid barew: burden, weigh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">eparkeitw: help, aid barew: burden, weigh down<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>ekklesia: church, congregation ontws: real<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: If any believing woman has widows, let her help them, and let not the church be burdened, so that they may help the real widows.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al pimpinan jama'at dong<bt>About/concerning leaders of the congregation</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Orang yang pimpin jama'at deng bae, bosong musti lebe hormat sang dia deng bayar dia pung gaji deng batúl. Lebe-lebe dong yang karjá banting tulang ko kasi jalás Tuhan pung Kata-kata, deng ajar sang bosong jalan idop yang batúl.<bt>(As for) people who lead the congregation/believers well, you-pl must give more honour/respect to him/her and pay him/her a true/correct/appropriate wage. Especially those who work extra hard (Idiom: throwing bones) to explain God1's Words, and teach you-pl the true/correct way of life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalws: well proistemi: rule, manage, conduct,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kalws: well proistemi: rule, manage, conduct, administer, lead<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>diplous: double time: honor, compensation, remuneration<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>aksiow: consider worthy kopiaw: become weary, work hard, labor<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>LITERALLY: The elders who rule well are worthy of double honor, especially the ones who work hard in the word and teaching;</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ada tulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo pake sapi ko inja kasi lapás padi dari dia pung tangke, na, jang ika mati dia pung mulu, ko biar dia ju makan.&gt;&gt; Deng ada tulis lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa karjá, na, dia pantas dapa gaji.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) it is written in God1's Holy Writings that, “If you use a cow to step on releasing rice/grain from its stalk, na, don't tie its mouth closed, so it can also eat.” And it is written elsewhere saying, “Whoever works, na, it is appropriate for them to get/receive a wage.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="irik = injak kasi jato biji"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">irik = injak kasi jato biji padi dari mayang (BI) ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Matthew 10:10. Use the 1 Cor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">Matthew 10:10. Use the 1 Cor 9:9 form. Check parallels. The second quotation may be a paraphrase of Numbers 18:31 or 2 Chronicles 15:7. bous: ox<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>aloaw: thresh phimow: tie shut<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: for the Scripture says, "Don't muzzle the ox when it is threshing"; and, The worker deserves his wages.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:4, Mateos 10:10, Lukas 10:7</note></p>
    <fig path="hk-lb\HK00096C.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top">Sapi inja padi-gandum<bt>Cow stepping on rice-wheat (generic-specific)</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Kalo ada yang tudu orang yang pimpin jama'at, na, jang tarima bagitu sa! Musti ada dua-tiga saksi yang omong sama, baru lu tarima ko urus sang dia.<bt>If there is someone who accuses a person who leads a congregation/believers, na, don't just accept it like that (=at face value)! There must be two-three witnesses who say the same thing, only then (should) you-sg accept (what they say) to deal with him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kategoria: accusation, charge, formal accusation, judicial"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kategoria: accusation, charge, formal accusation, judicial accusation paradexomai: accept, acknowledge<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>ektos: outside LITERALLY: Do not accept an accusation against an elder, except upon the testimony of two or three witnesses.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 17:6, 19:15</note><v n="20" />Kalo su togor sang dia, ma dia masi idop iko tarús deng itu sala, na, togor sang dia di muka jama'at. Deng bagitu, orang laen dong sonde barani iko-iko bekin sala bagitu.<bt>If/when you reprimand/admonish him/her, but s/he still lives continue to follow that wrong/sin, na, then reprimand/admonish them in front of the congregation. In that way, other people will not dare/have the courage/boldness to follow doing the same thing of that kind of wrong/sin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iko-iko = follow doing the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">iko-iko = follow doing the same thing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamartanw: sin enwpion: before|i(20) (20) |relegxw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hamartanw: sin enwpion: before<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>elegxw: expose, reprove, correct loiroi: the others, the rest<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>phobos: fear LITERALLY: Those who continue sinning, correct them in front of all, so that the rest may have fear.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Kasi jalan ini sarat samua dalam jama'at deng sonde pili muka, deng sonde barát sablá. Beta taro ini tugas di lu pung tangan di muka Tuhan Allah deng Yesus Kristus. Ana bua di sorga yang Tuhan su pili dong, ju jadi saksi!<bt>Carry out all these requirements in the congregation without prejudice, and without bias/favouritism (fairly). I place this work/responsibility in your hands in front of God, and Yesus Kristus. The *angels in heaven that God1 has chosen are also witnesses! [NOTE to daughter translations: If in front of is taken literally, or if "these works" is unclear /TA deng YK jadi saksi, bilang, sakarang beta taro ini tugas/pasan di lu pung tangan./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diamarturomai: charge, warn, adjure eklektos: chosen,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">diamarturomai: charge, warn, adjure eklektos: chosen, elect<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>phulassw: watch, keep [a law], observe [a law], follow, do, carry out xwpis: apart<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>prokrima: discrimination, partiality, favor, prejudgment, bias prosklisis: inclination, partiality, favoritism<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: I charge you before God and Christ Jesus and the chosen angels, that you carry out these things without partiality, doing nothing with favoritism.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Jang buru-buru angka orang ko jadi pimpinan. Pareksa bae-bae sang dia lebe dolo. Te kalo bosong angka orang sambarang, ais itu orang bekin sala, bosong ju iko pikol tanggong-jawab, tagal dia pung bekin-bekin. Jaga lu pung diri ko barisi tarús.<bt>Don't be in a hurry to elevate/install a person to be the head-leader. Examine him carefully first. Cuz (elaboration) if you-pl install just anybody, and then that person does wrong, you-pl also participate in shoulder.carrying responsibility, because of what he does. Guard yourself so that you are clean/pure continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jiplak = trace (picture, behaviour) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">jiplak = trace (picture, behaviour) ; tiru-tiru = copy, imitate</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xeiras: hands taxews: quickly, hastily|i(22) (22)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">xeiras: hands taxews: quickly, hastily<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>epitithemi: put upon koivwnew: share, participate in<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>hamartias: sin allotrios: to another<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>hagnos: pure terew: weakness<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: Do not lay hands on someone hastily, lest you share another persons sins; keep yourself pure.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang buru-buru angka orang ko jadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Jang buru-buru angka orang ko jadi pimpinan jama'at. Jang iko-iko orang laen pung sala. Ma jaga lu pung diri ko barisi tarús.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Beta dengar lu maen saki parú tarús. Lebe bae, mulai sakarang lu campor aer deng anggor sadiki, ko biar jadi obat. Jang cuma minum aer puti sa.<bt>I've heard that you often have stomach/abdomen sickness/pain. It would be good if beginning now you mix water with a little wine, as medicine/remedy. Don't just drink plain water.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta dengar lu maen saki-saki parú"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Beta dengar lu maen saki-saki parú tarús. Lebe bae, satu-satu kali lu minum anggor sadiki, jadi obat. Jang cuma minum aer puti sa.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hudropitew: drink water oinos: wine|i(23) (23)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hudropitew: drink water oinos: wine<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>oligos: a little khraomai: use<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>stomakhos: stomach puknas: frequent<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>astheneias: weakness, sickness, infirmity, ailment, illness LITERALLY: No longer drink water, but use a little wine for your stomach and your frequent illnesses.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Lia bae-bae! Ada orang yang pung sala dong kantara memang. Dong balóm sampe di hakim pung muka, ma samua orang su tau dong pung sala. Ma ada orang laen ju, yang lama-lama baru dong pung sala kantara.<bt>Take a good look! There are people whose wrongs/sins are immediately obvious/visible. Before they arrive in front of the judge, everyone already knows what they have done wrong. But there are other people also, who have a long time go by before their wrong/sin becomes visible/obvious.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prodelos: clear, conspicuous, obvious proagw: lead,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">prodelos: clear, conspicuous, obvious proagw: lead, precede, go before<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>epakolouthw: follow after, come later LITERALLY: The sins of some men are obvious, going before them into judgment, but certain ones follow after;<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Bagitu ju deng orang yang bekin bae dong. Ada yang kantara memang. Ma ada laen dong yang bekin bae sambunyi-sambunyi. Biar bagitu, ma apa yang dong bekin tu, lama-lama kantara ju. Sonde bisa sambunyi hal yang bae.<bt>It's the same way with people who do good. There are those who are immediately obvious/visible. But there are others who do good things in secret. Even that being the case, nevertheless what they have done, will eventually become obvious/visible. Good things cannot be hidden.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hwsautws: similarly prodelos: obvious|i(25) (25) |rkruptw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hwsautws: similarly prodelos: obvious<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>kruptw: hide LITERALLY: Similarly, the good deeds are obvious, and others cannot be hidden.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al budak deng tuan<bt>About/concerning slaves and masters</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Ada tuan pung budak yang parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Dong musti kasi hormat dong pung tuan, ko biar orang luar dong sonde ada alasan ko omong kasi jato Tuhan Allah pung nama, deng pandang enteng kotong pung ajaran.<bt>There are masters whose slaves are the ones who believe in the Lord Yesus. They must give respect.honour to their masters, so that outsiders have no reasons to speak bringing down God's name/reputation, and scorn/belittle/disparage our teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hosoi: as many as zugos: yoke|i(1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hosoi: as many as zugos: yoke<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>despote: master, lord, owner time: honor<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>aksios: worthy, deserving hegeomai: consider, think, regard, count<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>blasphemew: slander, speak evil of, defame, blaspheme LITERALLY: As many as are under the yoke of slavery, let them consider their masters worthy of all honor, that the name of God and the teaching not be spoken evil of.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2a" />Ada budak pung tuan yang parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Budak dong sonde bole pandang enteng dia pung tuan tagal itu tuan parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus. Karmana ju dong musti layani lebe bae lai dong pung tuan, tagal dong deng dong tu, sama-sama orang parcaya yang musti idop basayang.<bt>There are slaves whose masters are the ones who believe in the Lord Yesus. Slaves are not allowed to scorn/belittle/disparage his/her master because that master believes in the Lord Yesus. Even more they must serve their master even better, because they (slaves) and they (masters), are together/fellow believers who must live in reciprocal love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malahan ; Karmana ju = even"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">malahan ; Karmana ju = even more ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataphronew: think down on, scorn, despise,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kataphronew: think down on, scorn, despise, treat with contempt douleuw: serve, perform the duties of a slave, obey<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>euergesia: service, kindness antilambanw: benefit, take part in, devote oneself to, practice<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: And he who has a believing master should not look down on him, because they are brothers, but rather serve him, because those who benefit from their service are believers and beloved. Teach these things and exhort [them to do them].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ajaran yang sala, deng upa yang bae<bt>False/incorrect teaching, and good reward</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2b" />Tius! Ajar ini samua, deng kasi samangat jama'at dong ko bekin iko itu samua.<bt>Tius (Tim)! Teach all this, and encourage/inspire the congregation/believers to follow/obey all of it.</bt><v n="3" />Kotong pung ajaran yang batúl jadi dasar dari jalan idop yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Ma orang yang ajar laen dari ini, dong tu su tola buang Tuhan Yesus Kristus pung ajaran yang batúl.<bt>Our-inc true/correct teaching is the basis/foundation of a way of life that pleases God1's liver. But people who teach something different from this, they have rejected the Lord Yesus Kristus' true/correct teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heterodidaskalew: teach a different thing, teach"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">heterodidaskalew: teach a different thing, teach other doctrine eusebeia: godliness, godly faith, religion, piety<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>proserxomai: follow, agree with, accords with prosexw: pay attention to:<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>hugiainw: be healthy, sound LITERALLY: If anyone teaches different doctrine and does not agree with the sound words which are of our Lord Jesus Christ, and godly teaching,<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Orang macam bagitu, kapala bésar, ma otak kosong! Dong pung panyaki tu, andia suka cari-cari hal deng bakanjar so'al kata-kata sa. Ini samua bekin orang dong iri hati, babakalai, bekin rusak orang laen pung nama bae, deng bacuriga bodo-bodo sang orang laen.<bt>People of that sort, are arrogant/stubborn/rebellious (lit. big head), but empty brained! Their disease is liking to/always making disputes out of nothing (Idiom) and arguing/debating over just words. All this makes people jealous/hateful, fighting with each other, damaging other people's good name/reputation, and just suspicious of other people in silly/stupid ways.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sangka = suspect ; curiga ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">sangka = suspect ; curiga = suspicion ; @@ fixed ambiguity May 2005</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tuphow: puffed up, inflated, conceited, arrogant,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">tuphow: puffed up, inflated, conceited, arrogant, proud epistamai: understand<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>nosew: have a morbid craving, be ailing with, sick zetesis: investigation, controversy, discussion, debate, argument<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>logomaxia: dispute about words, word battle phthonos: envy, jealousy<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eris: strife, discord, contention, quarreling blasphemia: slander, defamation, blasphemy, harsh and abusive language<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>huponoia: suspicion, insinuations, conjecture, secret opinion poneros: wicked, evil, unjust, malicious, false<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: he is conceited, understanding nothing, but having a morbid craving for controversy and disputes about words, out of which come envy, strife, slander, evil suspicions,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Orang macam bagitu maen bekin kaco tar abis-abis. Dong pung pikiran busuk. Dong su sonde tau lai mana yang batúl. Dong pikir kalo dong rajin-rajin deng so'al agama, dong bisa jadi kaya.<bt>People of that sort keep upsetting things /causing disruptions/disorder endlessly. Their thinking is rotten. They don't even know any more what (of choices) is true/correct. They think that if they are industrious about religion, they can get rich. [NOTE to daughter translations: If you want to maintain lexical cohesion for /eusebia/ "godliness" between vs.3,5,6,11, try /Dong sala pikir, kalo dong rajin iko Tuhan pung mau, dong bisa jadi kaya/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***paragraph at 5b removed; See added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***paragraph at 5b removed; See added note above ; tato'a = bump into s.t., dead-end, jalan buntu, di buku bambu (Rote); pikiran busuk = can't think right if they want to; pikiran bengko</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diaparatribe: mutual or constant irritation, wrangling,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">diaparatribe: mutual or constant irritation, wrangling, dispute diephtheirw: spoil, morally ruined, depraved<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>nous: mind, attitude, way of thinking, mental and moral state of being aposterew: steal, rob, deprive<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>nomizw: think, imagine, consider, believe porismos: means of gain, means of profit<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>eusebeia: godliness, piety, LITERALLY: constant wrangling between men of depraved mind and deprived of the truth, imagining godliness to be a means of [financial] profit.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Memang, agama bisa bekin manusia rasa ontong bésar. Te idop yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati, campor deng orang rasa puas deng apa yang dong punya tu, itu baru agama yang batúl!<bt>It is true that religion can make humans feel great benefit/profit. Cuz (elaboration) a life which pleases God2, mixed with a person/people feeling satisfied with what they have, now that is what real religion is! [NOTE: In idiomatic Kupang--doesn't back translate well]. [EXEG: NRSV] [NOTE to daughter translations: If /agama/ creates too much noise, try /Ma iko yang batul, kalo orang idop bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati, ju rasa puas/cukup deng apa yang dong punya, itu bawa ontong besar, sama ke dong su jadi kaya./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed to get lexical cohesion for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***changed to get lexical cohesion for Key Term "godliness" w/vs.3 plus WITH contentment</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="autarkeia: contentment, soul sufficiency LITERALLY: But"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">autarkeia: contentment, soul sufficiency LITERALLY: But godliness with contentment is great profit.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te idop ta'ika deng Tuhan tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Te idop ta'ika deng Tuhan tu, yang bekin orang rasa puas deng apa yang dong punya. Itu baru agama yang batúl!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Inga bae-bae! Waktu barana sang kotong, kotong sonde bawa satu apa ju pi dalam ini dunya. Deng kalo kotong mati ju, kotong sonde bawa apa-apa kaluar dari ini dunya.<bt>Remember this well! When we-inc were born, we didn't bring anything into this world. And when we-inc die also, we don't take anything out of this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eispherw: bring in ekspherw: carry out|i(7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">eispherw: bring in ekspherw: carry out<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>dunamai: be able, can LITERALLY: For we brought nothing into the world, so that [as a result] we cannot take anything out;<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Jadi, asal ada cukup makanan deng pakean, na, puas deng itu sa!<bt>So (consequently), as long as there is enough food and clothes, na, just be satisfied with that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diatrophe: food, sustenance skepasma: clothing, covering|i(8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">diatrophe: food, sustenance skepasma: clothing, covering<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>arkew: be satisfied, content LITERALLY: and having food and clothing, let us be satisfied with those things.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma orang yang kapingin jadi kaya, gampang kaná goda macam-macam, deng kaná hiki kiri-kanan, tagal dong cuma pikir harta sa. Itu samua bekin calaka deng bekin ancor dong pung idop.<bt>But (as for) people who want/yearn to be rich, it's easy for them to be affected by various sorts of temptations/seductions, and be ensnared left-right, because they are only just thinking about belongings/possessions. All that causes misfortune and destroys their life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boulomai: desire, wish, want ploutew: be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">boulomai: desire, wish, want ploutew: be rich<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>empiptw: fall into, involved in peirasmos: test, temptation, enticement to sin<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>pagis: trap, snare, entanglement epithmia: desire, lust, longing [in a bad sense]<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anonetos: useless, thoughtless, devoid of sound reason, unintelligent, foolish, unwise, irrational blaberos: harmful, hurtful<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>buthizw: sink, plunge, drag down olethros: destruction, ruin, death, corruption<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>apwleia: destruction, utter destruction, annihilation LITERALLY: But those who desire to be rich fall into temptation and a snare and many useless and harmful desires, which plunge men into ruin and destruction;<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te cinta doi tu, jadi akar dari orang bekin jahat macam-macam. Ada orang saparu buru doi bagitu rupa, sampe dong su serong jao dari dong pung parcaya yang batúl. Deng bagitu, dong sandiri bekin ancor dong pung idop.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) loving money like that, is the root from people doing all sorts of evil. There are some people who pursue/hunt money in so many ways, to.point.that they have already strayed/diverged/deviated far from their true/correct belief. In that way they have destroyed their own lives.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hriza: root, beginning from which something"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">hriza: root, beginning from which something grows, source. Blass-Debrunner 273, definite predicate nouns preceding the verb are anarthrous (=theos een ho logos). So "the root" rather than "a root". kakos: evil, bad, moral evil<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>philarguria: love of money, avarice, miserliness oregw: aspire to, crave, strive for, desire, covet<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>apoplanaw: mislead, wander away, go astray, depart peripeirw: pierce through<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>odynee: pain, pang, sorrows LITERALLY: For the love of money is the root of all evils, from which certain ones having desired, have departed from the faith and pierced themselves with many pains.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pegang kuat-kuat ajaran yang lu su tarima<bt>Hold firmly to the teaching which you have received</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed to match 2 Tim 3:10"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***changed to match 2 Tim 3:10 title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Timotius! Lu ni, Tuhan Allah pung milik. Jadi ondor jao-jao dari samua yang jahat. Idop barisi. Idop ko bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati dalam samua hal. Parcaya tarús sang Yesus Kristus. Sayang samua orang. Batahan dalam susa. Idop manis deng samua orang.<bt>Timotius! You are God's possession. So (consequently), retreat/shy away very far from everything that is evil. Live clean/pure/holy. Live to please God1's liver in every matter. Continue to believe/trust in Yesus Kristus. Love all people. Endure/persevere in difficulty (=don't give up). Live sweetly (=politely) with everyone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed to get lexical cohesion with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***changed to get lexical cohesion with "godliness"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Compare Gal 5:23 pheugw: flee, shun,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">Compare Gal 5:23 pheugw: flee, shun, avoid, escape from, keep away from<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>diwkw: persue, aim at, strive for, seek after, aspire to dikaiosune: righteousness, uprightness [in the moral and religious sense]<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>eusebeia: godliness, piety, devout and entirely correct religious attitude pistis: faith<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>agape: love hupomone: endurance, patience, longsuffering, steadfastness, fortitude, perseverance<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>praupathia: gentleness, meekness, inner spirit resulting in meekness, gentleness of feeling LITERALLY: But you, o man of God, flee these things, and persue righteousness, godliness, faith, love, endurance, gentleness.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Idop iko Tuhan pung mau dalam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Idop iko Tuhan pung mau dalam samua hal.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Bajuang batúl-batúl, ko kasi jalan samua ajaran yang kotong parcaya. Tuhan su pange maso sang lu pi dalam idop yang sonde tau abis-abis. Jadi paló kuat-kuat itu idop, ko jang lapás. Deng lu su kasi tau lu pung parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus bagitu di orang banya pung muka.<bt>Make every effort (lit: struggle truly) to carry out/set in motion all the teachings that we-inc believe. God1 has called you to enter into eternal life (=that does not end). So (consequently), strongly embrace that life, and don't let it go. And you-sg have made known/told your faith in the Lord Yesus like that before many people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi badiri = tegakkan, erect, build"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">kasi badiri = tegakkan, erect, build up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agwnizomai: struggle, carry on a contest,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">agwnizomai: struggle, carry on a contest, strive, fight agwn: struggle, contest, athletic event<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>epilambanomai: grasp, take hold of, obtain tees aiooniou zooees: CHECK.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>kalew: call homologew: confess, declare, also V. 13 but in a different context (Jesus vs. people doing it); 1Cor 12:3, Rom 10:9, Phil 2:11<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: Struggle in the good contest of faith to obtain eternal life, into which you were called and confessed the good confession before many witnesses.</Message></Annotation><v n="13-14" />Deng sakarang beta minta lu ika janji bagini: bekin iko Tuhan Yesus pung parenta samua. Jang langgar satu parenta ju, ko biar orang sonde dapa lu pung sala. Bekin iko itu samua deng batúl, sampe deng hari kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus datang kambali. Beta minta ko lu janji bagitu di Tuhan Allah pung muka. Dia yang su kasi nyawa buat samua yang idop. Beta ju minta lu janji bagitu di Yesus Kristus pung muka. Dia yang su kasi tau tarús taráng so'al Dia pung diri di gubernor Pontius Pilatus pung muka.<bt>And now I ask that you bind a promise like this: follow/obey all of the Lord Yesus' commands. Don't violate/contravene/transgress even one command, so people can't find anything wrong with you. Do it all correctly/truly until the day when our-inc Boss, Yesus Kristus, comes back again. I ask that you promise that before God. He is the one who has given life.force to everything that lives. I also ask that you promise that before Yesus Kristus. He is the one who openly told about Himself before gubernor Pontius Pilatus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraggellw: encourage, charge, command, exhort, ggive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">paraggellw: encourage, charge, command, exhort, ggive orders, instruct zwogonew: give life<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>martureesantos teen kaleen homologian: testify, bear witness. To the truth, according to John; not to the Church's confession that Jesus Christ is Lord, as in 12. LITERALLY: I charge you before God, who gives life to everything, and Jesus Christ, who testified the good confession before Pontius Pilate,<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>UBS commentary: scope of 11-12 may be Timothy's ordination, his baptism, or the whole letter. tepew: keep, obey, fulfill<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>aspilos: without blemish, unstained, spotless anepilemptos: irreproachable, free from reproach, reproof<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>mexri: until epiphaneia: appearance<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: keep the commandment spotless, free from reproach until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ,</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:13-14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 18:37</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Tuhan Yesus yang hebat, Dia yang pegang kuasa!<bt>The Lord Yesus who is amazing/incredible, He is the one who holds power/authority!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia tu, Raja Bésar dari samua raja.<bt>He is the Big Raja from among all rajas.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia tu, Bos Bésar dari samua bos.<bt>And He is the Big Boss from among all bosses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bagitu pas dia pung waktu,<bt>And just at the right time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan mau bekin kantara ini hal dong.<bt>God2 is going to make these things visible/obvious. [EXEG: make active with God as agent (Knight, Carlton)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***make active with God as agent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">***make active with God as agent [Knight, Carlton],</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kairos: time, definite and fixed time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">kairos: time, definite and fixed time idios: ones own, appropriate, proper<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>deiknumi: show, point out, be manifest, reveal, make known makarios: for tunate, blessed, source of highest joy, state of true well being. 1:11.<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>monos: only dunastes: ruler<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: which in his times he will show, the blessed and only ruler, the King of kings and Lord of lords,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ini samua nanti kantara."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Ini samua nanti kantara.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Cuma Dia sandiri yang sonde kanál mati.<bt>Only He himself is the one who doesn't know/recognise/experience death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia idop dalam taráng yang manusia sonde bisa tahan lia.<bt>He lives in light which humans cannot stand/endure seeing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Sonde ada satu orang yang bisa dapa lia sang Dia.<bt>There is not one person who can see Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua hormat kasi sang Dia!<bt>All respect/honour is given to Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua kuasa ada di Dia pung tangan sampe salamanya!<bt>All power/authority is in His hands until forever!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Bagitu sa! Amin!<bt>That's how it is! Amin!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="silo = &lt; silau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">silo = &lt; silau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="athanasia: immortality phws: light. Knowledge? Lack"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">athanasia: immortality phws: light. Knowledge? Lack of sin? Purity? Not a successful metaphor for Pidgin speakers, but all over the Bible.<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>oikoew: dwell, inhabit aprositos: unapproachable, not able to be approached<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>time: honor, respect, esteem, reverence, worship, adoration kratos: power, rule, sovereignty<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: who only has immortality, dwelling in unapproachable light, whom no man has seen, neither can see; to whom is honor and power forever; amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al orang kaya dong<bt>Concerning rich people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Kasi tau orang kaya dalam ini dunya, ko dong jang sombong, deng jang tagantong di dong pung harta. Te itu harta dong samua nanti abis. Lebe bae dong tagantong di Tuhan Allah yang idop. Te Dia yang po'a kasi kotong samua yang kotong parlú, ko biar kotong bisa rasa ini idop pung sanáng.<bt>Tell the rich people in this world to not be proud/arrogant, and to not be dependent on their wealth/belongings. Cuz (elaboration) all that wealth/belongings will later disappear/end/be finished. It is better for them to be dependent on the God who lives. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who poured/overflowed to us-inc everything that we-inc need, so that we-inc can feel/experience the happiness of this life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plousios: rich, rich person aiwn: age|i(17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">plousios: rich, rich person aiwn: age<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>hupselophronew: be proud, [think high] high minded, haughty, proud, insolence elpizw: hope, set ones hope on<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>ploutos: wealth, riches adelotes: uncertainty, uncertain<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>parexw: grant plousiws: richly<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>apolausis: enjoyment LITERALLY: Charge those who are rich in this age not to be proud, nor to set their hope on uncertain riches, but [to set their hope] upon God who grants us all things richly to enjoy,<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Kasi tau sang dong ko pake dong pung harta ko bekin yang bae. Dong musti rajin bekin yang bae. Dong musti buka tangan ko tolong orang laen dong, deng suka bagi-bagi berkat yang Tuhan kasi sang dong.<bt>Tell them to use their wealth/belongings to do what is good. They must open their hands (=be willingly generous) to help other people, and like to/regularly divide out the blessings which God1 has given to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agathoergew: do good, practice doing things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">agathoergew: do good, practice doing things for others kalos: good<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>eumetadotos: generous, ready to share worldly goods koinwnikos: liberal, generous, fellowship of sympathy<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: to do good, to be rich in good deeds, to be generous, willing to share,</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Deng bagitu, dong kumpul ame harta ko jadi dasar yang kuat buat dong pung idop beso-lusa. Deng bagitu, dong bangun idop yang ada pung arti.<bt>In that way, they gather together wealth/belongings as a strong/firm foundation/basis for their life in the future. And in that way, they build/construct a life that has meaning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabung ; modal ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">tabung ; modal ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apothesaurizw: store up, store away, lay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">apothesaurizw: store up, store away, lay up. Sermon on the Mount, Matthew 6:19-20. themelios: foundation, basis for receiving good things<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>mellw: be destined epilambanomai: grasp, take hold of<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>zwe: life ontoos: real, true<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: storing up for themselves a good foundation for the time to come, that they may take hold of the true life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus konci dia pung surat<bt>Paulus locks (=closes) his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Tius! Jaga bae-bae samua yang Tuhan Allah su taro di lu pung tangan. Jang iko tasosok deng omong kosong dong. Jang iko batamba mulu deng bahasa yang sonde bawa hormat kasi Tuhan Allah. Inga, é! Te ada orang yang anggap dong pung diri pintar. Padahal dong pung &lt;pintar&gt; tu, sonde ada pung dasar apa-apa. Sonde usa pi basilat lida deng dong.<bt>Tius (Tim)! Guard carefully everything that God has placed in your-sg hands. Don't go along with involving yourself in nonsense/pointless chatter. Don't jump into contributing to talk which doesn't bring respect/honour to God. Remember, é! There are people who consider themselves to be smart/clever. When in fact, their ‘smartness’ has no basis/foundation whatsoever. There is no need to go debate with them. [NOTE to daughter translations: If UNS responses come back on “What is it that Timothy is to guard?” as “true teaching, message, people, Timothy's ministry” then it's fine. If they come back in a different direction, then narrow it to “carefully guard the message that God has placed...”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** review. If UNS responses come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** review. If UNS responses come back as "teaching, message, people, Timothy's ministry" then it's fine. If they come back in a different direction, then narrow to "carefully guard the message that God has placed..." ; ***"dirty talk deleted to broaden range covered by following clause batamba mulu = add words to, add into discussion;<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText=", 4:1, 5:8; phulassw: watch, guard,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">, 4:1, 5:8; phulassw: watch, guard, keep safe, protect paratheekee: entrusted, committed to 2 Tim 1:12, 14<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>ektrepw: turn away from, avoid bebelos: profane, godless, useless, profitless<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>kenophwnia: chatter, babble, empty talk antithesis: opposition, contradiction, objection<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>pseudwnumos: falsely called, falsely named gnwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: O Timothy, guard that which has been entrusted to you, avoid godless chatter and contradictions, which are falsely called knowledge,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang iko batamba mulu deng bahasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">Jang iko batamba mulu deng bahasa kotor dong, yang sonde bawa hormat kasi Tuhan Allah.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ada orang saparu yang parcaya itu ajaran putar-balek dong, sampe dong serong dari dong pung parcaya yang batúl sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>There are some people who believe in those deceptive teachings, to the point that they deviate from their true/correct faith/belief in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** serong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z">*** serong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta minta ko Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong samua.<bt>I ask that God1 show/demonstrate His goodness/kindness/grace to you-pl all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaggelomenoi: giving themselves out as experts,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:00:52Z" status="Information">epaggelomenoi: giving themselves out as experts, laying claim to expertise in knowledge astoxew: miss the mark 5:8 1:19 4:1<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: which some having professed concerning the faith, have missed the mark. Grace be with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saloom,<bt>Saloom,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>